title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix together and bake in
two 8 or 9-inch or one 9 x 13-inch pan which are greased and floured at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool.
Slice horizontally for torte effect, if you want that look.

title: roasted turkey
directions: Remove giblets from center cavity and neck cavity.
Wash turkey in cold water and dry inside and out.
Drain.
Salt both cavities, but not the outside.
Place onion and celery in both cavities.
Bend wing tips under back.
Place turkey on a rack, breast side up, and coat with shortening.
Rack with turkey on it should be in a large roasting pan with lid or an aluminum (disposable) one.
I use the disposable pans and I put 2 together so that the pan won't buckle when lifted.
Wrap foil around legs. Cover turkey with a foil tent.
Roast in a preheated 325° oven for 6 1/2 to 7 1/2 hours.
Remove turkey from oven and brush with glaze of melted jelly.
Place turkey on silver tray and garnish with parsley, pickled peaches, crab apples, cocktail corn or steamed asparagus.
Serves 18.

title: crock-pot sloppy joes
directions: Simmer hamburger, onions and celery for 1 hour.
Put this and all remaining ingredients into crock-pot for 4 hours on low.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook peppers 5 minutes in salt water and drain; set aside. Brown meat and onions in lard.
Add tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until rice is almost tender (5 minutes).
Add cheese.
Stuff peppers and stand upright in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with more cheese.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out bread dough.
Layer meat and cheese; sprinkle with oregano.
Bring sides to center and pinch together.
Pinch ends tightly, also.
Spread oil on baking sheet.
Place Stromboli on sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetables and clams over pasta
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add all the vegetables and cook until done.
Add wine and clams.
Heat and serve over pasta.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Spread potatoes evenly in a lightly greased baking dish. Spread evenly with sour cream.
Sprinkle with bacon and green onions.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: easy salad
directions: Combine tomatoes and onion.
Add salt, sugar, vinegar and hot sauce.
Yields 4 servings.

title: belgian beef
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons salad oil in a large skillet. Brown beef, a few pieces at a time. Brown quickly and remove from pan. Add 2 tablespoons salad oil and onions. Brown well.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except bread.
Mix with beef in skillet and bring to a boil.
Place in 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° until beef is tender.

title: company potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place mixture in 13x9 pan.
Take 1 cup bread crumbs and add small amounts of butter just to moisten.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on mixture.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl, except brown sugar and chopped pecans.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle the brown sugar and chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well and pour into greased iron skillet or muffin pans. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Bread is very moist.

title: good time potato soup
directions: Place potatoes, carrots and onion in kettle.
Cover with water and cook until soft.
Season to taste and add milk, bacon and potato flakes to thicken it.
Makes 8 large servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg (for juicy pie, omit flour).
Add sugar mixture to the sliced apples, toss to coat fruit.
Fill a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate with apple mixture; dot with butter.
Adjust top crust, seal and flute edge.
Sprinkle with sugar on top if desired.
Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove foil, bake for 20 to 25 minutes more or until crust is golden.
Cool or serve warm with ice cream.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix together.
Use regular crust or graham cracker crust. Makes 2 pies or a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Let cool.
Crumble half the cake into small pieces and place in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix pudding with
cups
milk.
Pour 1/2 of pudding over cake in bowl.
Add 1 can pie filling (smooth over).
Add 1 can pineapple and layer of 1 1/2 cups bananas. Repeat. Crumble cake, add pudding
over
cake, add
pie
filling	(smooth
over), 1 can pineapple and layer of 1 1/2 cups bananas. Top with Cool Whip, cherries and pecans. Chill.

title: mountain cobbler
directions: Mix and pour in center of melted margarine.
Put fruit in center of pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: al and berniece's chili(large amount)
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add brick chili.
Then add spices, juice, tomato soup, vinegar, catsup, onions and peppers.
Simmer several hours.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Heat milk, water, oil, sugar and garlic salt to lukewarm.
Add dry yeast to 2 cups flour in mixer bowl.
Pour liquid mixture over dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and beat.
Add grated Cheddar cheese.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour with spoon.
Makes a thick dough.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions, salt, and peppers in large pan and cover with lots of ice cubes. Let stand 3 hours. Drain well; do not rinse. Mix the rest of the ingredients and place over medium heat and cook until cucumbers get yellow. Put into jars while hot.

title: fresh strawberry dessert
directions: Mix; press into 8 x 12-inch pan. Bake 12 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk in large bowl.
Let stand 1 hour. Add brown sugar and egg; mix well.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to oat mixture.
Stir in oil and 1/2 cup raisins (optional).
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: canned squash
directions: Boil liquids.
Add squash; boil 1 minute.
Put in hot jars and cover with liquid.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix meat, rice, egg, 1/2 cup tomato juice, onion and seasoning.
Form into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Put into large skillet with lid.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: turkey sausage
directions: Add all ingredients together and mix thoroughly.
Fry a patty or two and sample it.
Increase ingredients, if necessary.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Combine the first three ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes in a small pan.
Combine all ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter in heavy pot.
Add milk and blend.
Add sugar, stirring constantly and bring to boil.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add morsels and heat until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and continue heating until well mixed.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into greased dish.
Yields 4 pounds.

title: 3 layer congealed salad
directions: Prepare 1 flavor jello as package directions; pour in bowl and let congeal.
Dissolve 1/2 pack of yellow jello in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Dissolve marshmallows in other 1/4 cup boiling water.
Mix cream cheese (softened) and mayonnaise; mix with yellow jello and dissolved marshmallows.
Pour this mixture over first flavor; let congeal.
When set, prepare other flavor of jello according to package directions.
Pour over second layer and let set until firm.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip on top.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix together cornstarch and cold water. Heat fruit with syrup in saucepan until hot.
Add cornstarch and water mixture and stir into fruit.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring the while.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole and dot with the 1 tablespoon butter.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto hot fruit.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: rice, peanuts and cranberries
directions: Boil rice with chicken bouillon cubes; drain off 9/10 of water, then put in peanuts, then put in cranberry sauce.
Eat cold or hot.

title: cousin betty's charleston pecan pie
directions: Melt syrup, sugar, butter and salt slowly.
Gradually add to eggs.
Add vanilla slowly.
Put pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
A family favorite.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Grease and flour your pan before you bake.
Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; add pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Pour in tube pan and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup of tomato sauce mixture and stir thoroughly.
Place meat mixture in pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie glaze
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil and boil approximately 3 minutes or until clear.
Stir in Jell-O; let cool. Place strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour mixture in pie shell. Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: little red chicken
directions: Place chicken in 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine other ingredients.
Mix well and pour over chicken. Bake in uncovered dish for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: maritata
directions: Beat butter until very soft, then beat in cheeses and egg yolks.
Gradually mix in cream.
Heat chicken broth, water and wine to boiling.
Add pasta, broken into 1/2-inch lengths.
Boil gently 8 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and add coconut.
Pour into baked pie crust; top with meringue and sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 400° for 8 or 10 minutes or until meringue is lightly brown.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save 6 tablespoons juice. Mix pineapple and remaining juice, sugar and flour. Add cheese and margarine. Stir well. Bake 20 minutes at 325°. Crumble Ritz crackers and add the 6 tablespoons of juice. Mix well and put on top of casserole. Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: clam dip
directions: Whip all together until creamy.
Let stand for an hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together good.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Add marshmallows and mix.
Chill.

title: hal's deer stew
directions: Lightly flour, salt and pepper meat.
Brown in fry pan with grease.
Remove meat.
Add enough flour to absorb grease in pan. Let brown, stir.
Add can of soup and 1 can water to pan.
Stir to make gravy.
Add Lipton soup; stir well.
Place meat back in pan. Add salt to taste and pepper.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes; stir to prevent sticking.
Add peeled, cubed potatoes, carrots and celery. Cover and simmer until meat is tender, stirring.
Simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours, longer - better.
May use crock-pot

title: pillsbury hot roll mix kalacs
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in lukewarm water in a cup until mixture foams up.
Heat milk to lukewarm and add butter.
Stir until melted and then add eggs.
Mix well; add yeast mixture. Combine with flour mixture thoroughly; knead well.
Form into a round mold and place in a greased bowl.
Cover with a towel and set in a warm place to rise for 1 hour.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick, spread with nut filling.
Roll up, folding ends under. Place in a well-greased baking pan and brush top with beaten mixture of 1 egg yolk and 1 teaspoon milk.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour in warm place.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: asian barbecued duck
directions: Prick duck all over with a fork.
Place them in a steamer with an inch of water; simmer for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove; cool duck. (Can be done the day before barbecue.)
Cut duck into serving size pieces.
In a food processor, combine all ingredients and puree. Marinate the duck pieces in puree for 1 hour.
Barbecue duck by placing a drip pan in center of barbecue and placing hot coals around it.
Place duck in center over drip pan, put lid on barbecue and cook until skin is brown and duck is done to taste.

title: crumble top pumpkin gingerbread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, whole wheat four, sugar, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
With a pastry blender or fork, cut until it resembles coarse meal.
Set aside 2/3 cup.

title: no-bake peanut butter balls
directions: Combine powdered sugar and butter in a large mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in peanut butter and cereal, mixing with hands if needed.
Shape dough into balls. Chill.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with cooked and drained seashell pasta.

title: baked corn
directions: Put oleo in baking dish and melt until hot.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: quick pasta e fagioli
directions: Heat oil in a heavy medium sauce pan over medium heat.
Add onion, celery and carrot and saute, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes.
Add broth and water.
Cover and bring to boil.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Add garlic and pasta and cook, uncovered, over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, 5-8 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Save nicest berries out whole. Mash up ripest berries and mix with sugar and cornstarch. Bring to a boil and cook until clear (about 5 minutes). Stir constantly. Add red food coloring and butter. Stir in whole berries and pour into cooled pie crust. Chill overnight. Top with whipped cream.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jacket.
Peel and cube (small) while still very warm.
Mix onion salad mix with salad oil, vinegar and water. Pour over warm potatoes.
Add salt, pepper and celery seed.
Mix.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: In food processor, process cheese and add melted margarine. Transfer to bowl and add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Chill.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Put pecan half on top and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: anginetti
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add the pineapple, Cool Whip and sugar.
Cut the cookies in half.
Fill and let stand in refrigerator 8 hours.
(If desired, pineapple may be substituted with a small package of frozen/thawed strawberries.)

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Trim pork chops.
Cut slits in chops almost to the bone to form pockets.
In a saucepan, cook the onion and bell pepper in the margarine until tender.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients. Spoon 1/4 of the stuffing into each pork chop.
Secure the pockets with wooden toothpicks.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pineapple in 2-quart casserole. Mix sugar, flour and cheese and sprinkle over pineapple.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Pour melted butter over casserole. Bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth. Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and a little garlic in butter. In saucepan melt together cheese, soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients together and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Saute beef in skillet with onion, garlic and green pepper until beef is light brown and onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, sugar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat. Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese is melted. Serve warm with tortilla chips or Fritos.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mary's banana cake
directions: In a large bowl, mash 2 bananas until soft. Add butter, sugar, eggs, and vanilla and beat.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in water until done; drain.
Add other ingredients and stir until well distributed.

title: easy hamburger veggie soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in large, heavy stainless steel pot until meat is no longer pink and onion is clear.
Add to meat mixture and stir the pearl barley, ground black pepper, garlic granules and thyme.
Add stewed tomatoes, sugar, carrots, butter beans or green lima beans, Great Northern beans or green beans, frozen corn, potatoes and chicken broth.
When these ingredients are cooked until tender, add frozen peas and noodles or pasta.

title: beef noodle soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain.
Stir in V8 juice, soup mix, contents of noodle seasoning packet and mixed vegetables.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer uncovered until vegetables are tender.
Return to a boil; stir in noodles.
Cook 3 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for 5 minutes.
Add ground meats, eggs, onion, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, allspice and nutmeg and refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour.
Shape into balls and bake for 15 minutes or until browned.
Put in crock-pot.
Add 1/2 can of beef consomme, pepper and remaining salt.
Cover and cook 4 to 6 hours on low, 2 to 3 hours on high.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Bake in loaf pans.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, soup and seasonings together and put into a Pyrex dish.
Melt butter and mix with crackers and almonds and sprinkle on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp christmas tree
directions: Thaw
frozen
shrimp.
Place
shrimp
in
boiling
salt water. Cover and	simmer	about 5 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Then
drain.
Peel shrimp, leaving the tail section of the shell on.
Remove sand veins and wash.	Chill.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt butter and pour off excess, reserving it for later use.
Put chicken mixture in baking dish.
In medium bowl, mix reserved butter, Bisquick and milk with an electric mixer. Mixture will not be smooth.
Pour batter over chicken. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Cut in squares to serve. Yields 8 servings.

title: joy's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk and flavors to butter mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine together; add 1 egg at a time. Add vanilla flavoring, sugar and then flour. Pour all into a greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until done.

title: easy-tasty ham roll-ups
directions: Mix horseradish with cream cheese.
Spread dollop of mixture on slices of ham or luncheon meat.
Roll up.
Secure with toothpicks and chill several hours.
Before serving, slice into bite-sizes.
Good served with Fritos.

title: nan's divinity
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved; then cook without stirring to 255° (hard-ball stage). Remove from heat and pour, beating constantly, in a fine stream into egg whites.
Continue beating until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss. Add
vanilla and pecans.
Drop quickly from tip of teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Chop cheese, peppers, onions and tuna real fine.
Add olives, butter and tomato sauce and mix.
Cut off tops of rolls and remove centers.
Fill with mixture and wrap each roll in heavy waxed paper.
Twist ends securely, place in paper bag and heat in slow oven (300°) for 20 minutes.
Serve at once.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients, place over top of meat.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.
Remove cover, bake 1/2 hour more.
Can use lamb riblets or chicken legs also.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Butter a 10 x 6 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch glass baking dish.
Adjust rack 6 to 7 inches above bottom of oven.
Preheat oven to 350°. Toast bread lightly, then spread with butter while warm.
Cut slices in halves.
Fit neatly in baking dish, overlapping.
Scald milk.
Beat eggs in a 2-quart bowl.
Stir in salt and all but 2 tablespoons of sugar, then hot milk, then vanilla.
Pour over toast and let stand for 10 minutes, pressing down on toast lightly to absorb milk mixture.
Blend cinnamon with remaining sugar and sprinkle over top.
Bake directly on oven rack, 25 to 30 minutes, or until pointed knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: coconut or egg custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter, flour, milk and vanilla.
For egg custard, pour into pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
For coconut, follow steps and just add coconut to ingredients.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Make roux with flour and oil.
Add all other ingredients except pie shells.
Season to taste.
Cooke 1 hour.
Add mixture to 2 pie shells.
Top with other 2 pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon horseradish sauce
directions: Combine ingredients. Perfect complement to prime rib or seafood.

title: chili con queso
directions: Heat all ingredients over low heat.
Add 2 pounds cubed Velveeta cheese and heat until just melted.
Remove from heat. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each egg.
Add bananas.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda together.
Add flour mixture to banana, mix alternately with sour cream.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning mix. Simmer 5 minutes. Drain. Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and place in large bowl. Add tomatoes, onions, chips and Cheddar cheese. Add meat mixture. Toss gently to mix. Serve with taco sauce and/or sour cream. Yield: 8 servings.

title: potatoes in orange shells
directions: Wash yams.
Place in large saucepan.
Cover with boiling water. Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes; let cool.
Peel.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°.
Remove pulp from oranges (could use a grapefruit knife).
To potatoes, add sugars, orange peel, orange juice, margarine, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pile in orange halves.
(For a decorative touch you might cut a zigzag design in top edge of orange shell with kitchen scissors.)
Pile in orange halves.
Warm potatoes in oven.
Put a marshmallow on each orange half and heat until brown.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, using electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Reduce speed to low and gradually beat in flour, oats and zest.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: dough(empanadita)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Slowly add water, stirring until well blended and doughy.
Divide into 12 patties; flatten thinly between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Place 2 teaspoonfuls meat mixture on each patty.
Fold diagonally and seal. Brown in hot oil, turning once. Serve hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hobo dinner(makes 4)
directions: Make 4 patties from hamburger and lay on a large square of aluminum paper.
Sprinkle 1/4 of potatoes, onions and carrots over patty.
Put a couple spoons of margarine on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Wrap well and pinch corners.
Put into a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pork chops men love
directions: Dredge chops in mixture of the flour, salt, dry mustard and onion powder.
Brown chops in oil in skillet.
Place browned chops in crock-pot.
Add soup (no water).
Cover; cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 3 1/2 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat again; add baking soda, flour and vanilla.
Mix (will probably need to use hands).
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Take out a little while to soften, then roll into balls (size of quarter).
Put on greased cookie sheet, press flat with a potato masher and cook at 325° until light brown.
Makes a lot of cookies.

title: prune cake and sauce
directions: Mix and cook at 350° on sheet cake.

title: strawberry fool
directions: Wash berries and set aside 4 small nicely shaped ones for garnish.
Stem and core the remaining berries and cut them into thick slices.
Sprinkle with sugar.
How much sugar will depend on how sweet the berries are, the bourbon and the orange zest.
Cover and set them aside to marinate for half an hour.
Mash the berries to a pulp with a potato masher.
(Do not use a blender or food processor; both machines will liquify them.)

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix the vinegar and sugar on stove until dissolved, not boiling.
Add the oil and pour over rest of ingredients.
Will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Serves 20.
Great for holidays.

title: b. b. pie crust
directions: Put all ingredients in pie pan.
Stir with fork.
Press out into pie pan and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Add margarine and mash.
Mix rest of ingredients to squash mix and pour into casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs, if desired, and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: magic-in-the-middle cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in flour.
Place half of the dough in a cookie press, using the ribbon plate.
Press strips onto ungreased cookie sheets.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into a greased Bundt or tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli crock-pot casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot
and cook on slow for 1 hour or until ready to eat.

title: veggie bars
directions: Lightly grease bottom of jelly roll pan and spread crescent rolls (about 1 1/2 cans).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until brown. Flatten with a spoon as baking.
Mix cream cheese, dressings and seasonings and spread on cooled rolls.
Add veggies and press into mixture.
Add cheese and cut into squares.	Serve.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix flour, oil and salt and pepper to taste.
Drench chicken pieces in mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Fold ingredients all together; pour in graham cracker crust. Chill and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease pans.
Cream butter with the sugar; add the eggs and beat well.	Add the mashed bananas, stirring to blend.
In a separate bowl, sift together the dry ingredients.
Fold the dry ingredients
into the batter, mixing well.	Add the nuts. Pour the batter
into the pans and bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 or 5 small loaves.	For muffins, fill
muffin cups 3/4 full and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in ground beef; saute until brown.
Mix in broth, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Spread mashed potatoes over meat mixture, sealing to edge of dish.
Run fork over potatoes for rippled surface.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake until potatoes are brown, about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: dora's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Mix cream of coconut and milk.
Pour on hot cake (poke holes in cake).
Cool completely. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Very moist and delicious.

title: edie's cookies(pecan balls)
directions: Mix dry ingredients and butter with nuts.
Make walnut sized balls and bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Roll in confectioners sugar twice, once when hot, then again while warm.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Spread over ham slices.
Roll lengthwise; cut into pinwheels.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: chicken ronnie
directions: In medium casserole dish, line bottom of dish with dried beef. On top of beef, place chicken breast, side by side (leaving about 1/2-inch space between each).
This will make it easy to serve later.
Fold together sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour this mixture evenly over chicken.
Now sprinkle on layer of bacon bits.
Place, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
Cream together with electric mixer the shortening, sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Add mashed ripe bananas and walnuts to creamed mixture.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Divide mixture in half.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Heat butter, Coke, cocoa and marshmallows to a boil.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture; mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla; beat well.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Ice while hot.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients. Mix sugar with mayonnaise and spread over vegetables. Top with cheese. Sprinkle with bacon bits. Make a day ahead and refrigerate.

title: filled sugar cookies(in honor of jerry landess)
directions: In a large bowl, cream the sugar and shortening.
Then add the egg and mix well.
Next, add the vanilla, baking powder, soda and salt and mix well.
Add the milk and mix well again.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough that will roll easily.
Roll and cut with a round cookie cutter (perhaps 2 1/2 inches).
Dough should be rolled out to at least 1/8-inch thickness.
Have the dough chilled and the board very lightly floured for rolling.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients and form into a loaf. Put in Dutch oven and place potatoes (quartered), sliced carrots, green pepper, onion, celery and the tomatoes around meat.
Cover vegetables with water and bake at 350° until done.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray pan with nonstick spray.
In bowl, combine cheeses, eggs and spices.
Mix well.
Take cooked noodles and spread cheese in middle and fill.
Roll noodles and place in dish.
Spoon sauce over noodles and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes and garnish with parsley.

title: coconut cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Add shortening and 1/2 of milk; beat for 2 minutes.
Add remaining milk, flavoring and unbeaten eggs.
Beat another 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 layer cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool and frost.

title: peas in white sauce
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into large chunks.
Cook potatoes with margarine in 3 cups of water until just done.
Add green peas the last 6 minutes of cooking.
Remove from heat.
Combine cornstarch with 1 cup of cold water, stirring until smooth.
Add to peas slowly while stirring.
Stir until blended.
Return to medium heat just until sauce is desired consistency.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pat's czech dumplings
directions: Boil chicken pieces in large pan of water.
Salt to taste and add garlic (for seasoning).
After chicken is cooked, remove and debone; set aside.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Clean mushrooms and separate stems. Chop stems and mix with Swiss cheese.
Place mixture in a mushroom cap.
Sprinkle with Hi-Energy Soup Supplement and a small amount of water over each mushroom.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: diet tomato dressing(28 calories per tablespoon)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Slowly beat with beater.
To keep from separating, refrigerate.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender in 5 or 6 cups water; drain.
Remove meat from bones and cube.
Discard skin and bones.
Crush tortilla chips and spread in a 2-quart casserole.
Add chicken.
Blend remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour over chicken; top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Sift
together
the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk and
salad oil, stirring quickly and lightly until mixed. Do not beat.
Saute
onion.
Add tomato juice.
Bring mixture to a
boil. Drop
in dumplings and simmer 10 minutes with the lid off,
then 10 minutes with the lid on.
Serve dumplings in tomato and onion juice sauce.

title: peanut clusters candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, marshmallows, margarine and salt in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate chips, vanilla and peanuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in hot milk.
Combine ingredients, folding in egg whites last.
Place in a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with creamed peas over the sliced salmon.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt oleo, oil and marshmallows in pan over low heat.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring often.
Add popped corn, peanuts and M&M's to mixture.
Mix together and put into greased pan.
(May use tube or oblong.)
Allow to set about 1/2 hour.
Turn onto dish and refrigerate.

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Put roast in crock-pot.
Mix mushroom soup, water and onion-mushroom soup mix together.
Pour over roast and cook on high about 6 to 8 hours (depending on size of roast).

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook enough chicken breasts to make at least 3 cups chopped chicken.
Reserve liquid.
Cook 1 package Uncle Ben's chicken flavored rice, using broth for liquid.
Add 1/3 cup mayonnaise mixed with 3/4 teaspoon curry powder, 12 stuffed, sliced olives and 3 cups chicken (chopped).
Cut artichokes in half and line bottom of 2-quart greased casserole.
Pour chicken-rice mixture over artichokes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Casserole is much better if mixed up the day before it is baked.

title: pesto cheese spread
directions: Mince parsley and basil in food processor until fine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Process until smooth.
If using as a dip, add more milk until right consistency.
Place in sourdough round and serve.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and boiling water.
Set aside.
Add oil to cereal mixture.
Mix together flour, salt, sugar (you can use less sugar than suggested) and soda.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk; mix well.
Stir in cereal mixture.
Add raisins, nuts, dates or other fruit.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kentucky pecan cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in order listed.
Beat until smooth. Stir in pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour mixture into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Invert pan and cool cake completely; remove from pan.
Sprinkle top of cake with powdered sugar.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pie crust for a 9-inch pie. Beat 4 egg whites until foamy.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar slowly. Beat until meringue makes soft peaks.
Set aside.
In another bowl, cream butter and remaining sugar.
Add egg yolks and flour. Beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice, grated rind and milk slowly. Beat.
Fold into meringue.
Pour into pie shell and bake 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown onion and hamburger.
Drain.
Add pizza sauce and mushrooms.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
To make crust, combine flour, milk, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt white chocolate and stir in marshmallows until melted. Then stir in peanut butter and Rice Krispies, spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Refrigerate until firm and cut in squares.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Cook according to box directions. When thick remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted. Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: chicken and wild rice salad
directions: Have cooked rice chilled or at room temperature.
Combine this with the chicken, grapes, nuts, artichokes and water chestnuts. Add salt and mayonnaise and toss gently to blend thoroughly. Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 8.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins.
Peel when warm and cut up as desired.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add diced onion.
Brown bacon, remove from pan and break into small pieces.
Add to potatoes.
Add flour to bacon grease and stir until smooth.
Add vinegar and water to flour mixture and stir until it bubbles. Then add sugar, stirring thoroughly, until the mixture has a clarified look or transparent.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand overnight, if possible, to let flavors permeate the potatoes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables as listed. Top with crumbled bacon. Mix mayonnaise and cheeses. Spread on top of salad.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together apples, sugar and nuts.
Let stand for 1 hour. Add dry ingredients to apple mixture with wooden spoon.
Mix.
Add oil; mix.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix.
Spoon batter into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely on rack.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: african chicken
directions: Boil chicken; let cool and debone, then return to pot. Add rest of ingredients except peanut butter. Half hour before serving, simmer for another 15 minutes; serve with rice or noodles.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Top with Ritz crackers and melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: patti's porcupines
directions: Mix meat, rice, water, onion and seasonings.
Form into 4 medium or several smaller balls.
Fry in shortening until crusty. Add tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Cover and simmer 45 minutes over low heat.
Add water, if needed. Serves 2.
Can double recipe.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans together and pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix up cake according to directions on box and pour this over coconut and pecans.
In saucepan, melt butter and cream cheese over medium heat and gradually add powdered sugar.
Blend well.
Pour this evenly over the rest of the cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overcook; will burn easily.
Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread in milk until all milk is absorbed by bread.
Mix thoroughly with ground beef and add egg.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mixture is very soft so you must use tablespoon to handle. Form into balls by dropping heaping tablespoonfuls into flour, then shape into balls.
Brown lightly in butter.
When browned, add to 1 can tomatoes, small onions, potatoes, carrots, celery and green peppers if you like.
Simmer about 1/2 hour until all is done.
Will serve 8 people nicely.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder and chili powder.
Cook shells and cheese as directed on box.
Drain.
Add to meat and cook.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Blend together and serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until hard ball stage (about 8 minutes).
Put Marshmallow Creme in mixing bowl and stir in hot syrup.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix eggs and milk in bowl.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder in bowl.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Heat oil to 350°. Pour 1/2 cup batter into funnel and fry until golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: coconut pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; bake and cool.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage and green onions.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together cheese, sugar and margarine.
Add pinch of soda to flour.
Add eggs and flour alternately, beating well after each addition.
Mix vanilla into batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured tube pan.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet lightly.
Combine butter Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoons of dough 2-inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes, then remove.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix eggs, Parmesan cheese and oleomargarine. Stir into
cooked
and
drained spaghetti.	Spray 9 x 13-inch casserole
dish
with
Pam.
Spread
spaghetti mixture into pan. Spread
12	ounces	of cottage cheese over mixture. Pour 32 ounces of
meat flavored spaghetti sauce (Ragu, Prego or equivalent) over cottage
cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in hot 350° oven. Remove from oven and spread 8 ounces of grated Mozzarella cheese over
spaghetti
sauce
and bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven and let
set
15 minutes.
Cut into squares. Serve with garlic bread and green salad.
(Delicious.)

title: hamburger and noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and hamburger.
Add soup, water and seasoning. Cook five minutes.
Add a drop of oil to water in which noodles are cooked.
Pour hamburger mixture over cooked noodles in a greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: white sauce(one cup)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and dash of white pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.

title: bean salad(no oil)
directions: Combine vinegar, water and sugar.
Bring to
a	boil and simmer for 3 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Drain all canned vegetables and
combine with celery, onion and
green
pepper.
Pour vinegar mixture over and refrigerate overnight.

title: jiffy dessert
directions: Bake cake per package directions in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for about 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix pudding and 1 cup milk.
Add softened cream cheese and gradually add other cup of milk.
Spread over cake.
Drain pineapple and spread over pudding layer.
Then spread Cool Whip over top and garnish with maraschino cherries (red and green at Christmas) and nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: walnut roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add water to cover.
Add catsup, chili powder, salt and pepper; simmer until done.

title: my holiday veggies
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower in salted water; drain well. Saute mushrooms in butter for a few minutes.
Juice will come out of mushrooms.
Keep this in pan.
Add your cream cheese, cut up. Melt on low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add lemon juice and milk; stir well.
Fold in broccoli and cauliflower. Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.
You may top with buttered crumbs, if desired.
We like it best without the crumbs.

title: sausage strata
directions: Trim crust from bread and fit bread into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex dish.
Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Stir in mustard.
Spoon sausage evenly over bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese and sausage.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dream bars - coconut
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla and sugar together.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour on to crust and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm.
Can be rolled in powdered sugar.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together and add alternately with buttermilk and bananas to creamed mixture.
Add lemon juice, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cocktail cream puffs
directions: In a 2 to 3-quart pan, stir water and butter over medium-high heat until butter is melted.
Add flour all at once, stirring until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball (about 2 minutes).
Remove from heat and cool briefly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in cheese.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Then add 1/2 cup cheese.
Place in 8 x 8 dish.
Top with remaining cheese and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.	Great served with chili.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and cherries.
Blend on low speed 15 seconds.
Increase to medium and blend 30 seconds. Stir in cherries and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured mini bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix first 5 ingredients together well and put in bottom of baking dish, spreading evenly.
Then place your chicken pieces on top of your other ingredients.
Then sprinkle soup mix over top of chicken evenly.
Seal tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours. Do not peek!

title: white fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and cream.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallow cream and nuts. Pour into greased pan.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
Let cool. Prepare jello according to box directions.
Poke holes in the top of cake.
Before jello solidifies (while still runny) pour over cake.
Refrigerate until cold (about 1 hour).
Top with whipped topping.

title: thick and creamy cheesecake
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Add to cream cheese.
Mix at low speed.
Add egg until well blended.
Slowly add heavy cream, then vanilla.

title: dottie's carrot cucumber relish
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Let stand for 3 hours. Drain well.
Combine and boil the sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Add vegetables; simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour into sterile pint jars; seal and place in water bath for 5 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 pints.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Dredge steak in flour mix.
In large skillet, brown steak in hot oil.
Remove steak and set aside.
Add onion and garlic to skillet.
Cook until tender.
Add steak, broth and wine.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with noodles or rice.
May add sliced mushrooms if desired.

title: hot cashew chicken salad
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients; place in casserole.
Place grated cheese over top as desired.
Crush potato chips on top. Bake until cheese melts, approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water and strawberries.
Let sit in refrigerator until just starting to gel.
Add pineapple and fold in Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator until sets overnight.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all together with hand mixer.
Pour into ice cream freezer and process.

title: peanut patch chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add hot water during cooking if necessary.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: italian sausage and zucchini
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven, put 1/4 cup oil, 1 medium onion (diced), green peppers, zucchini, salt, pepper, basil, oregano and garlic.
Simmer until all ingredients are fairly tender.
Add about 6 nice tomatoes (scaled and quartered) and 1 can mushroom pieces. Cook until it becomes a thick sauce.
Add more tomatoes as it cooks down.
Cut up Italian sausage.
Boil off in water and add to sauce. Cook about 10 to 15 minutes longer.
You can serve this as is or over rice or noodles.

title: chicken salad sandwich
directions: In bowl, combine chicken, celery, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and pepper.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and serve with ice.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Makes its own crust.
Put in blender and mix on high for 5 seconds.
Stir down and mix again for 5 seconds.
Pour in pie plate and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Done when knife comes out clean.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Put in refrigerator until cool. Makes delicious spread for sandwiches on rye bread. Serve with pickled onions or sweet pickles.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Cut Twinkies in half.
Put 1/2 in bottom of dish.
Top with pudding, then pineapple.
Top with remaining Twinkies, then with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put in casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: jewish chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients by hand.
Mix until blended, but do not overmix.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
May be frosted, but good plain.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream Crisco and sugar in large bowl.
Add boiling water to Crisco mixture and stir until dissolved.
Add beaten eggs and yeast to Crisco mixture.
Sift flour and salt into mixture.
Mix well.
Cover bowl with Saran Wrap and refrigerate to use as needed.
Roll dough about 1/4-inch thick and cut with small cutter.
Dip dough into melted butter; fold over and place in pan.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Recipe may be divided.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat all ingredients except 7-Up.
Mix well.
Add 7-Up and beat well.
Pour in 13 x 9 pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening.
Cool slightly.
Beat the eggs until light and creamy.
Add the sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to eggs and sugar.
Stir in the chocolate and pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
While still warm, cut into bars.

title: cheddar cheese bread(bread machine)
directions: Put all the ingredients in the inner pan in the order for your pan and select bread setting, light setting, and start.

title: chocolate butterscotch heroes
directions: In a large saucepan, cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat stirring frequently, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt, over hot (not boiling) water, chocolate and butterscotch morsels, stirring constantly until smooth.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Chill until smooth, about 15 minutes.
Makes 48 bars 2 x 1-inch.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve red Jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cranberry sauce and mix well.
Chill until thickened.
Add apples, celery and nuts.
Serves 10.
When using double recipe, use only 1 c. pineapple juice.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake.
Slice cake in small 1/4 inch slices.
Using a big bowl place the following ingredients in layers.
Place all of cake slices in bottom of bowl.
Top with:
chocolate pudding, Heath bars and Cool Whip, then repeat.
Top with remaining Heath bars. Refrigerate overnight or 6 hours.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat until pudding consistency. Place in pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff and put on pie. Bake until meringue is slightly brown in 375° oven.

title: chocolate coconut bonbons
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine and milk together.
Add coconut and pecans.
Refrigerate.
When set, roll into small balls. Refrigerate again until balls are firm and ready to coat.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate using a fork or toothpicks.
Keep chocolate warm while dipping.
Makes about 130 pieces.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Wash navy beans and run them through hot water.
Put beans in large boiler with water and ham hocks.
Boil slowly, covered, for around 3 hours.
Braise onion in a little butter.
When onion is brown, add it to the soup mixture.
Serve real hot.
Add salt and pepper only after you put soup in individual bowls.
Serves 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line pie pan with crust.
Cream Crisco and vanilla.
Gradually add sugars beating after each addition.
Add beaten eggs in thirds, beating after each addition.
Thoroughly blend in chopped pecans, corn syrup and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Arrange pecans halves over top of filling.
Continue to bake for 35 minutes. Cool thoroughly.
Goes well with ice cream.

title: batter fried fresh vegetables
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in medium bowl; stir to mix.
Add egg and enough liquid to make batter the consistency of pancake batter.

title: cornbread dressing for boiled or baked chicken or turkey
directions: Break cornbread and white bread into small pieces; add other dry ingredients, then add eggs and onion.
Mash with potato masher. Add gradually 2 1/2 cups of hot broth and cream of chicken soup. If this is not enough, add more.
The amount of cornbread will make a difference.
Also, you will need to debone your chicken or turkey and place it in your mixture at this time.
Stir well, then cook at low temperature until done (about 350°).

title: sauce for ham
directions: Melt butter over low heat in medium saucepan.
Blend in flour. Remove from heat and add apple juice and raisins.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Place a slice of pineapple on ham slices and pour sauce on top.

title: pea-noodle salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve immediately.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pound sirloin or tenderloin very thin and cut into near finger-shaped pieces.
Melt half the butter in a large heavy pan. Add onion, cook and stir until onion is tender.
Add beef; cook quickly, about 5 minutes, browning on all sides.
Set aside.

title: june's layered salad
directions: Layer bottom of glass dish with sliced or broken lettuce.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and spices.
Add sugars and cream thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add rolled oats and raisins and mix.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add one-half of flour to creamed mixture and then sour milk.
Add remaining flour, mixing well.
Drop cookie mixture from spoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water with a fork until foamy.
Add pecan halves and mix with 2 forks until coated.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add milk.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Add crushed vanilla wafers.
Cook in a two pound loaf pan or tube pan about 1 or 1 1/4 hours at 300°.

title: anytime party dip
directions: Mix beans and taco sauce together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Mix tomato sauce and chili powder with meat mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Spread on top of beans.
Spread tomato bits on top of mixture.
Top with cheese. Heat in oven to melt cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: orange balls(no cook cookies)
directions: Mix crushed wafers, sugar and pecans.
Pour melted oleo over mixture and mix well.
Add orange juice that has been thawed and mix well.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls in Angel Flake coconut.
Put in icebox for 2 to 3 hours or leave overnight. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cranberry-raspberry ring
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add raspberries (still frozen). Chill until cold but not set.
Carefully pour in carbonated beverage.
Turn into 5-cup ring mold. Chill at least 4 hours. Serve with Miracle Whip, sour cream, Cool Whip or combination that suits your fancy.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Cook shells and peas until shells are tender; drain.
Add cheese, tuna, salt and pepper.
Serve right away.

title: steak diane
directions: With meat mallet, pound steaks to 1/3-inch thickness. Sprinkle one side of steak with salt, pepper and some of the dry mustard; pound into meat.
Repeat with other side of steak.

title: easy baked chicken kiev
directions: Place chicken breasts, one at a time, between 2 sheets of wax paper or plastic wrap.
With flat side of a mallet, gently pound breasts until each is about 1/4-inch thick; set aside.
In a rimmed plate or pie pan, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, 1 teaspoon of the oregano, garlic salt and pepper; set aside.
In a small bowl, stir together the 4 tablespoons softened butter, parsley and remaining 1/2 teaspoon oregano.
Spread about 1/2 tablespoon of the herb-butter mixture across each breast about an inch from lower edge; lay a strip of Jack cheese over butter mixture.
Fold lower edge of breast over filling, then fold in sides and roll up to enclose filling.
Dip each bundle in the melted butter and drain briefly; then roll in bread crumb mixture until evenly coated.
Place bundles, seam side down, without touching, in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Drizzle with any remaining butter.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or until next day.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 425° oven for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink when lightly slashed (cut just a small slash so filling doesn't ooze out).
Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: microwave ratatouille
directions: In microwave saute onions and garlic in olive oil in 2 to 2 1/2-quart, covered casserole on High for 4 minutes.
Add eggplant, pepper and zucchini.
Cover and cook on High for 7 minutes, stirring once.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Mix lightly.
Cover with towel and microwave for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serve over rice.

title: ham finger sandwiches
directions: Slice entire package of dinner rolls in half. Cream margarine, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, poppy seed and chopped onion together. Spread evenly over bottom half of rolls. Layer ham and Swiss cheese over creamed mixture. Cover with top of rolls. Bake in aluminum roll pan at low temperature until warm and cheese is melty.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine spinach, cheese, butter, bread crumbs and 1 beaten egg.
Roll into balls.
To other egg, add water and seasoning and beat.
Dip spinach balls into additional bread crumbs, then into egg mixture and again in bread crumbs.
Brown balls on both sides in margarine.
Serves 4.

title: magic cookie bars(makes 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt Land O Lakes sweet cream butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: tex-mex quiche
directions: Sprinkle chili powder over the inside of the pie shell. Combine cheeses with flour and place in pie shell.
Combine eggs, cream, chilies, olives, salt and pepper; pour over cheese.

title: house of grace tea
directions: Mix lemon, sugar, instant tea with lemon, white grape juice and water.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Add all ingredients into blender.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: no guilt brownies
directions: In large bowl combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, applesauce and vanilla and blend well.
Spoon batter into 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix pudding mix, milk and cream cheese together; spread on cooled cake.
Spread well drained pineapple over pudding mixture. Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate cake.

title: chocolate topping
directions: Add ingredients together in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick.
It's great on ice cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Line baking dish with bread slices.
Put peaches on bread. Now, cover peaches with more bread.
Mix margarine, eggs, sugar and flour together.
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: homemade crackers
directions: Sift flour, salt, and baking powder into a bowl. cut in butter until very fine. Add the milk and egg and mix to a stiff dough. Knead thoroughly and then toll dough very thin. Cut into squares or rounds and place on lightly buttered cookie sheets. Prick the crackers with a fork and then bake in a 400 degree oven for 10 minutes or until very lightly browned. If desired, crackers may be sprinkled with coarse salt.
Soda Crackers- follow the basic recipe, but substitute sour milk for sweet milk, omit the baking powder, and add 1/2 tsp. soda.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Place hamburger, tomato, water, sugar, salt, celery and onion in when hamburger is browning in large soup pot. When browned add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer on low till heated through.

title: pasta with sausage and peppers
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in frying pan over medium-high heat. Slice sausage and cook until brown on both sides.
Remove and drain.
Add 1 tablespoon oil and the onions and cook until golden. Add peppers; cook until soft.
Add garlic; drain and chop tomatoes and cook 1 minute.
Add sausage, salt, pepper and oregano.
Bring to boil, cover and reduce heat.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Remove cover and simmer until liquid thickens, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook spaghetti and serve with sauce.

title: pat's appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk; stir in dried beef, onion, green pepper and pepper.
Mix well; stir in sour cream.
Spoon into an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice; mix well. Sift together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour mixture into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 to 3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Flip on a tea towel which has been sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Roll up in towel and cool.
When cool, unroll and spread with the following cream cheese mixture: cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and butter.
Blend until creamy.
Spread on pumpkin sheet cake and re-roll.
Chill before slicing.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: sister dena's bunuelos(crispy sugar tortillas)
directions: Pour flour in a large bowl.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add baking powder, cinnamon, sugar and a dash of salt; mix together. Add hot water slowly, a little at a time, until you have a soft dough.
Put on a floured cutting board and knead for 5 minutes until not sticky.
Put in a plastic bag for about 10 minutes and set aside.
Make small balls of dough as in making tortillas. Roll out and lay on cloth until dry.
Fry them in hot oil.
Drain and sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.

title: pretzel jello
directions: *Can also use graham cracker crumbs.

title: tex-mex dip and chips
directions: Layer 1:
1 to 2 cans bean dip.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Add sugar, vanilla, vinegar and baking powder.
Beat well. Fold in crackers and pecans. Spread into 9 x 13-inch dish and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°. Let cool.

title: dutch baby
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch glass pie pan, which has been sprayed with vegetable spray.
Whisk well eggs, flour and milk in a mixing bowl.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 475°; until golden brown.
Cut into wedges and dust with powdered sugar or cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: sweet potato casserole(for microwave)
directions: Mix and place in 2 1/2-quart dish.
Cover and cook on High for 5 minutes; halfway through, stir mixture.
Can use probe after stirring.
Cook until casserole reaches 150°.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Cut franks lengthwise into 4 strips each.
Also, cut pepper and onion into thin strips.
Mix water, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and sugar together.
Place franks, pepper and onion into shallow casserole.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, about 45 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill for an hour before serving.
Serves 6.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except cereal and peanut butter in saucepan.
Cook for 2 minutes after mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and pour over cereal mix. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.

title: butterfinger freeze
directions: Soften ice cream and mix with crushed candy bars. Pour mixture over graham cracker crust in a rectangle 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze. Fifth Avenue or other candy may be used.

title: pizza crust
directions: Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly in a 425° oven.
(For 2 pizzas, use 12 to 14-inch pans.)

title: chocolate butter bars
directions: Mix together and set aside.

title: 7 layer green salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order given.
Top with cheese, then bacon. Pour dressing over all.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer bag of Tater Tots in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown sausage or hamburger; put meat over Tater Tots.
Mix the 2 cans of soup and water; put over meat.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Cut Velveeta cheese in cubes.
Heat all ingredients together.

title: lemon or vinegar salad
directions: Break lettuce into pieces. Add tomatoes, chopped green pepper and cucumber, in size desired.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Mash bananas.
Add lemon juice, then sugar, pineapple, cherries, sour cream, Cool Whip and pecans.
Freeze.
This keeps well.
Slice or cut into squares.
Serve frozen.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Slice potatoes into 1/8-inch rounds.
Layer half of each ingredient in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, then layer the other half.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Bake uncovered for the last 10 minutes until the potatoes are tender.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onions, celery and pepper in butter.
Add flour gradually and cook 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and thyme.
Add the chicken bouillon to water, then add to flour mixture.
Add vegies and clams with pimento and simmer 30 minutes.
Add (half and half) cream before serving.

title: sliced frozen fruit salad
directions: Freeze can of fruit cocktail.
Open both ends of can; push fruit cocktail out.
Cut into 4 slices.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with whipped cream.
Serve immediately.

title: brown bread
directions: Use 1 1/3 tablespoon vinegar in each cup of milk to make it like sour milk.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake and remove bones and skin from cans of salmon.
In a bowl, mix along with salmon the liquid from the cans along with milk to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
To this, add rest of the ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Spoon lightly into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: free and easy chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together and put chicken breasts on bottom of casserole dish.
Pour mixed ingredients over chicken breasts and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Chicken should bake uncovered.

title: "congo bars"
directions: Mix together.
Spread in cookie sheet and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.
Cut in squares when cooled.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, milk, eggs and chips in a large bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and continue cooling on plate.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: potatoes with creamy dill sauce
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet.
Add flour, salt, and dill. Stir to mix.
Do not let this mixture brown. Stir in buttermilk and cook until mixture thickens slightly.
Add the cooked potatoes and mix. Taste and add more salt, if needed.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put one box whole berries in baked pie shell.
Take either box and put in saucepan with sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick and clear.
Take off fire and add lemon juice.
Cool, then pour over berries in crust.
Top with whipped cream, Dream Whip or Cool Whip.

title: salsa
directions: Chop up the tomatoes, green onion and jalapenos.
Pick the leaves off the stems of cilantro and chop the whole bunch.
Then mix all together.
Enjoy.

title: creamy potluck potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, covered, in boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain again.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together condensed soup, sour cream, cream cheese and butter-flavored mix.
Add 1/4 cup of the shredded Cheddar cheese, 3 tablespoons of the green onion, the skim milk, parsley, garlic salt and pepper.
Stir to combine.
Stir in the cooked potatoes.
Transfer to a 2-quart shallow casserole or rectangular baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with remaining green onion.
Makes 10 side dish servings.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Layer as given in order.
Cover tightly at least 8 hours or overnight and toss when ready to eat.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat margarine, Crisco, eggs, bananas and vanilla flavoring; beat well.
Add flour; mix well.
Add nuts; stir good.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Warm soup and gelatine on low heat. Remove from heat.
Combine onions, celery, shrimp, salt and mayonnaise and add to soup.
Add softened cream cheese and pour into a mold and refrigerate.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter, vanilla extract, salt and sugar together. Gradually add flour and cornstarch until mixture forms a dough. Divide into 5 equal parts.
Roll each on lightly floured board into cylinder shape.
Divide into 1-inch sections.
Roll dough into ping-pong size balls.
Press down with fork.
Garnish with slices of red and green maraschino cherries.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until edges turn golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes and serve.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: friendship cake
directions: Pour 1 pint of starter into a glass gallon jar.
If no starter is available, substitute 1 1/2 cups brandy or mixed fruit juice. Add sliced peaches (cut each slice into 4 pieces).
Add juice.
Add cups sugar.
Stir each day for 10 days.
Cover the jar with a saucer and leave at room temperature.
Do not cover with lid or refrigerate.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients all together, blending well.
Chill 5 to 8 hours.

title: french chicken and broccoli soup(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk and cornstarch.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Stir milk and cornstarch together until smooth and stir into simmering soup.
Cook and stir until bubbling.

title: chili egg quiche
directions: Beat eggs slightly, stir in flour and baking powder. Add cottage cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, and green chilies. Pour into greased pan (9 x 13). Bake 35-40 minutes until done at 350 degrees. Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: salmon cheese loaf
directions: Flake salmon in bowl, removing all bones. Add all remaining ingredients, except peas. Mix well. Pour into lightly greased crock-pot or shape into round loaf. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour. Turn low and cook for 2 hours. Last hour, add peas around the loaf.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Combine soups; bake corn bread. Crumble cooled corn bread.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray and place chicken pieces in bottom.
Pour combined soups on chicken.
Sprinkle with pepper, then top with crumbled corn bread.
Salt broth to taste; pour on corn bread.
Slice margarine and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creamy raisin spread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in chopped pecans; let cool.
Serve with Melba rounds or use as a sandwich spread.

title: hot ham and cheese rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss with mayonnaise and chili sauce. Mix well. Spoon into hot dog rolls. Wrap each in aluminum foil, twisting ends securely. Bake 10 minutes in hot oven at 400°. These can be made ahead and kept in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal caramel bars
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture.
Pat remaining in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When done, sprinkle chocolate chips and walnuts over crust.
Drizzle ice cream topping over it.
Sprinkle reserved crust mixture and bake 30 more minutes.

title: apple slices
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in butter until size of peas. Combine beaten eggs, lemon juice and cold water; add to flour mixture.
Divide dough into 2 sections and roll 1 section to fit a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Go up the sides of pan with dough.
(Top dough pinch together on all sides.)

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large skillet, bring the broth and oil to a simmer over medium heat. Add onions and carrots; cook about 4 minutes, until onions are tender. Add the mushrooms, garlic, salt and pepper and cook for a few minutes, until most of the liquid has evaporated. Transfer this mixture to a large bowl and let cool. Add beef or turkey to this, along with bread crumbs, apple, parsley and sage. Add the egg and mix well, using your hand. Shape into 2 loaves and place in a lightly greased baking pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. When done, cover loosely and let set 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over crushed pineapple; stir well.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and nuts (if desired).
Mix well and chill.
Ready to serve.

title: sweet strawberry cake
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Mix pudding with milk as directed on package.
Add sour cream.
Pour pudding over cake and then add pie filling.
Mix cake with pudding and pie filling; then top with Cool Whip.

title: middle east eggplant spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pierce each eggplant with fork; place in a shallow casserole.
Bake until eggplant begins to look like it is imploding.
Skin should be puckered, and eggplant looks convex.
Remove from oven; cool until it is easy to handle.
Slit eggplant and scoop out pulp into food processor.
Process until it is pureed.

title: butter dips
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan, melt butter in oven.
Remove pan from oven.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk until dough forms, about 30 strokes.

title: brie with a pastry wrapper
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar to thick consistency.
Add walnuts and raisins.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Dissolve brown sugar, butter and granulated sugar with milk. Cook until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Add cornstarch dissolved in a little cold water.
Remove from stove and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Wash dried beans and soak overnight. Place in large Dutch oven. Add 3 to 4 quarts water, ham, onion, beans, garlic and salt and pepper. Simmer slowly uncovered for 3 to 4 hours until beans are soft. Serve over cooked rice.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook vermicelli according to directions but do not rinse.
Mix next 3 ingredients and toss well on vermicelli.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Chop onions, pepper and celery.
Add this mixture with pimento and olives to vermicelli.
Add the mayonnaise.
Better if let set.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix peas which have been drained, pimento, egg and soup in a baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Cover with cracker crumbs and continue to bake until the crumbs are brown.

title: skillet chicken mozzarella
directions: Cut green pepper into pieces; slice onion and set aside. Pound chicken breasts thin.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat chicken breasts with mixture.
Cook chicken in oil until nicely browned; remove from pan.

title: apple-oat muffins
directions: Soak oats in milk for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven at 400°. Grease 12 muffin tins.
Add egg, oil, molasses and apple to the oats mixture.
Mix well.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add the flour mixture to the oats mixture. Stir until just combined.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: holiday yam patties
directions: Put yams in layers in baking dish.
Cut butter over yams. Pour sugars over yams, then sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: appetizer avocados with hot bacon sauce
directions: In a small saucepan over medium heat, cook 2 tablespoons water and the first 5 ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Arrange avocado slices on 6 small plates.
Spoon on hot sauce; sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: fettuccine with crab, bacon and prosciutto
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook bacon until fat is rendered. Transfer bacon with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. Discard all but 3 tablespoons fat.
Add onion and saute over moderate heat for 5 minutes.
Add garlic and Prosciutto, cook for 1 minute longer.
Stir in tomatoes and wine, simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
May be prepared in advance up to this point.
Add crabmeat and cream, heat through.
Season with pepper to taste. Fold in parsley and bacon.
Serve hot over fettuccine.
Serves 6.

title: red punch
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 1 gallon.
Freeze colored water in a jello mold and let float on top of punch.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sparkling punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine lemonade and orange juice.
Add water, punch and one tray of ice cubes.
Stir occasionally.
Just before serving, add soda or ginger ale.
Yield:
30 to 35 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Chop vegetables together.
Mix last five ingredients together. Combine the chopped together and the mixed together items and let stand in fridge for 24 hours.
Before serving, stir gently.

title: low-fat pumpkin pie
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients; beat just until smooth. Pour into crust. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°; bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until
a knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: zucchini pineapple
