directions: Remove peelings and seed from zucchini and grate or dice.
Mix all ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Pour hot zucchini into clean, hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Process 30 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: real chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in oil, add garlic and simmer 30 minutes.
Combine all other ingredients and simmer, covered, for 1 hour or more.
Serve with dollop of sour cream.

title: ham and broccoli quiche
directions: Sprinkle ham, cheese, broccoli, onion and green pepper over bottom of greased 10-inch quiche dish; set aside.
Place Bisquick in large mixing bowl.
Whisk in milk, eggs, salt and pepper. Pour Bisquick mixture over ingredients in quiche dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center of quiche comes out clean.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin custard(low calorie)
directions: Beat eggs and combine with pumpkin until well blended.
Add sugar substitute; stir in milk and spices until thoroughly blended.
Pour pumpkin mixture into an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool pie.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving equals 90 calories or 3/4 bread, 1/2 meat and 1/4 milk exchanges.

title: diet salad dressing
directions: Mix well flour, dry mustard, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, vinegar and cold water.
Stir briskly until it boils.
Add liberal chunk of butter.
Add catsup, if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: old-fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Cover shanks with
water, heat to boiling, add bay leaf and peppercorns.
Reduce
heat.
Cover	and simmer 1 3/4 hours or until tender.
Remove
meat
from
the
stock
and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Strain
stock
into large saucepan.
Add meat and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes
or until carrots are tender.
Makes 8 servings (1 cup each).

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Work together with enough canned milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll out thin.
Leave to dry for 30 minutes.
Cut into strips.
Drop into your favorite broth.
Cook until done.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Heat Rotel and soup.
Melt in Velveeta cheese; then add cooked sausage.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown Italian sausage; drain.
Roll bread out 2 times length and width of dough.
Spread heavily with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with Italian sausage; cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up short ends to short ends.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Spread top with butter.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs, milk, sugar and spices well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over mixture. Drizzle margarine over cake mix and sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: crisscross peanut butter
directions: Cream shortening in bowl; add peanut butter and stir until blended.
Measure flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking powder. Add gradually and beat in granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until it is well mixed.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift and add dry ingredients in thirds and stir just until blended.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll them between palms into small balls.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten each ball by pressing with tines of fork to make crisscross pattern.
Dip fork in flour to prevent sticking to dough.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on racks.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and bake until brown and firm to the touch.

title: tomato barbecue chicken
directions: Fry chicken until brown.
Drain off most of shortening.
To drippings in pan, add the top ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pie crust(two 9-inch crusts)
directions: Sift flour; cut in shortening.
Add water and sugar.
Mix dough with fork until all the water is used.
Gather dough and press into a ball.
Roll out and line pie pan.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat all together and then fold in Cool Whip; let set in fridge.

title: florentine dip
directions: Mix all together.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes.
Stir gently every 2 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt together in a small bowl.
In a large bowl, combine other ingredients.
Add flour mixture and stir until blended.
Drop spoonfuls of dough on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Cook 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften dry yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Scald milk.

title: frozen punch
directions: Boil first 2 ingredients until syrupy.
Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale, and mix well.
Pour into 2 plastic gallon jugs.
Freeze.
Thaw 2 1/2 hours before serving.
Add 1 1/2 quarts ginger ale to each slightly thawed gallon of frozen mixture.
Mixture should be slushy.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: In a large skillet or kettle, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender-crisp.
Stir flour into zucchini.
Set aside.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and serve with raw vegetables.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and 1/4 cup water. Add 1 cup noodles, tuna, celery, cashews and onion. Toss lightly.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with mandarin orange sections. Serves 4 to 5.

title: fluffy hot cakes
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Bake on griddle until fluffy and brown.
Turn only once.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in pan.
Sprinkle cornflake crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown around edges.

title: cheesy cauliflower
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in salt and pepper. Remove from heat; stir in 1 c. cheese and set aside. Place cauliflower in a greased 2 1/2 qt. casserole. Pour cheese sauce over cauliflower. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 c. cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Heat chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until melted, stirring. Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large bowl. Using a bowl with a lid, add 10x sugar.
Close lid and shake until coated.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In very large bowl mix 3 cups whole wheat flour, 3 cups white flour, salt, sugar and yeast.
Make a well and add water and oil. Mix well.
Add remaining flour, about 2 cups at a time.
Knead about 15 minutes on floured board.
Let rise in greased bowl until doubled in bulk; punch down and let rise again.
Shape into 4 loaves and let rise.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 40 minutes.
Remove loaves from pans and cool on racks.

title: kentucky-style scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice raw potatoes (according to size of dish used; same for frying pan). Butter baking dish. Layer potatoes, salt, pepper and a bit of onion. Sprinkle with a bit of flour. Continue until dish is full.
Heat milk (1 quart if large dish).
Pour over potato dish.
Can put grated cheese on top, if desired.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve liquid.
Simmer in a large saucepan over medium heat for 5 minutes 1 cup of pineapple juice, vinegar, sugar, cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Add drained pineapple chunks and continue heating 5 minutes.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 days.
Serve in a clear glass bowl, with frilly toothpicks.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles; drain and cool.
Brown ground beef.
Add sauce to meat and warm.
Slice eggs.
Layer sauce, noodles, grated brick cheese, sliced eggs, Parmesan, Ricotta, noodles, sauce, etc., in a lasagne pan or a deep 10 x 13-inch pan.
Put plenty of sauce on top to keep from drying out.
Sprinkle top liberally with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour and egg into mixing bowl.
Fold in butter, baking powder, sugar, peanut butter and salt.
Mix well.
Cook at 325°.

title: hot sauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg is added.
Mix cocoa and sifted flour. Add alternately with buttermilk.
Then add vanilla.
Last beat in soda mixture.
Grease three 9-inch cake pans and add just enough batter to cover bottom of pan.
Layers should be thin.
Bake in a 375° oven.
This makes 6 thin layers.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Mix together and drop on baking sheet and bake at 375 degrees until done.

title: ham and broccoli casseroleroswell, new mexico
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Spread in ungreased baking dish.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients with mixer or hand beater until smooth.
Slowly pour over cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour in 13 X 9 X 2-inch pan.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk.
Crush wafers and mix rest together.
Pour milk mixture over all.
Mix well.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan and chill.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Stir all together thoroughly, but avoid making a dust cloud. Use a large bowl and a slotted spoon.
Store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter marshmallow bars
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and marshmallows over hot water. Place cereal in large bowl.
Stri in peanut butter mixture.
Blend well.
Spoon into 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan rubbed with margarine. Cool in pan and cut into bars.
Yield:
18 bars (1 1/3 x 3-inch).

title: roasted potatoes and kielbasa
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Pour olive oil into large oblong baking dish.
Add thick sliced potatoes, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper. Toss well until well coated.
Bake in hot oven 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add sliced kielbasa, stirring well.
Put back in oven and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: sweet rolls coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and lukewarm water together. Mix together milk and butter.
Put 5 cups of flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl, making a well in center.
Mix together egg, milk, butter and dissolved yeast.
Pour in center of flour mix with wooden spoon until you can't mix.
Pour out on remaining flour, mixing and kneading until smooth.
Put into greased bowl.
When double in size, work down.
Let rise again.
Now it can be made into rolls, coffee cake, or cinnamon rolls.
Bake rolls at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: make-ahead chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove skin; cut meat from bones.
Spread cooked broccoli in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken meat over broccoli.
Spread undiluted soup over the chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over soup.
Melt margarine in a pan over low heat.
Add croutons, turning until coated. Spread croutons over baking dish contents.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until heated through.
Can be prepared ahead of time and baked just before serving time.

title: okra fritters
directions: Mix all together and add a little flour.
Cook like pancakes in a greased pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Divide everything in half. Crumble half sheet cake in bottom of punch bowl. Spread half of pudding over cake. Add half of other ingredients in order given. Repeat for second layer. Garnish with cherries or any way you wish. Refrigerate.

title: all-time favorite lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 9-inch square baking pan with foil and lightly coat with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine flour, sugar and lemon peel in bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in margarine until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Gradually add ice water, tossing with fork, until pastry is moistened (pastry will still be crumbly).
Firmly pat pastry evenly on bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: *Or 2 cups whipping cream, whipped and sweetened.

title: sweet and pungent beef
directions: Saute beef cubes in hot oil until browned all over.
Add carrots and green peppers and simmer 5 minutes.
Add pickles, cherries and pineapple.
Lower heat and let simmer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Mix ingredients and pour into dish. Set in pan of water and cook until firm (about 1 hour) at 350°.

title: spicy pork chops
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper and cinnamon on each side of the pork chops.
Spread approximately 1 teaspoon frozen orange juice on each pork chop.
Pour golden mushroom soup with water added over chops and simmer about 45 minutes.
Serve with Pilaf Rice.

title: chocolate and peanut butter truffles
directions: In saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with butter or margarine.
Stir in cocoa until smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk and vanilla; cook and stir until thickened and well blended about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Chill 2 hours or until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in chopped nuts or powdered sugar.
Chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil, butter and sugar and then add eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Then add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Press with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until it is set.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in 13x9 in. pan.
Let cool.

title: mother's homemade mayonnaise
directions: Beat egg yolk, then add Wesson oil, a few drops at a time, beating until mixture begins to thicken.
Then add oil more rapidly alternating with the lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients while beating.
Pour into a covered jar.
Refrigerate. Makes about 1/2 pint.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spritzbaaken
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs; gradually add in flour.
Stir in vanilla.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form into balls. Put in casserole dish.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil.
Stir until moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate chip puff cookies
directions: Beat on high egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix and add pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful onto brown paper covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into bite size balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: blueberry crumb bars
directions: Prepare shortbread crust; preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Reduce speed to low, beat in flour just until combined;
with fingers press dough firmly onto bottom of 15 x 10 1/2 jelly roll pan to form crust.
Bake 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Cool slightly on wire rack.
While crust bakes, prepare blueberry filling.

title: goulash
directions: Boil shells until tender.
Cook hamburger until brown.
Get a pot and put 1 layer of meat, about an inch thick, then add on top of that a layer of shells, then 1 can of tomato sauce, then 1 layer of shredded cheese, then repeat process again.
After done, put aluminum foil over it.
Cook at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: easy chicken and biscuits
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of celery soup

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimento, pepper and 1/2 of the crumbs.
Pour into a 9 x 13 casserole dish and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35-40 minutes.
Yields 6-8 hearty servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and make a well in dry ingredients to add liquid.
Stir enough to moisten.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: millionaires
directions: Roast pecans in microwave 5 minutes at 70% power.
Melt caramels with milk.
Butter waxed paper.
Stir pecans into caramel mixture.
Drop from teaspoon onto buttered waxed paper.
Leave several hours, then dip in chocolate.

title: cranberry raspberry mold
directions: Pour boiling water over jello in a bowl, stirring until jello is dissolved. Chill until very thick, but not set. With rotary beater, beat in sour cream and cranberry sauce. Pour into 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking dish. Chill until firm.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip onion rings into batter and fry until golden brown.

title: super bowl cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together at medium speed for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Fold in the nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin whoopie pies(makes 3 dozen sandwich pies)
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add pumpkin and eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, soda, vanilla and spices.
Mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Make sandwiches from 2 cookies filled with Whoopie Pie Filling.

title: sweet potato yams
directions: Put potatoes in baking dish.
Take the juice and mix it with the sugar.
Pour over the potatoes.
Slice the butter on top. Sprinkle the nutmeg over yams.
Then put the marshmallows on top. Top with a little nutmeg again.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Put potatoes in baking dish. Add onion.
Put drained beef over this.
Add mushroom soup, water and seasonings.
Cover and bake for 45 to 60 minutes in 400° oven. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken tortellini soup
directions: In an 8-quart stock pot, brown the chicken; season to taste. Add chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Add carrots; boil 10 minutes. Add onions and broccoli.
Bring back to a rolling boil.
Add tortellini; cook until pasta is done.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Cook Karo, brown sugar, salt and butter for 4 1/2 minutes on Full power.
Stir in soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn in a large brown paper bag.
Put in microwave for 1 minute.
Shake well.

title: bean dip
directions: Mash beans.
Add Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 of the peppers. Mix well.
Put into baking dish.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, cheese and rest of the peppers.
Stir well.
Put on top of bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lazy daisies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream the butter, gradually adding sugar and creaming well. Blend in egg, lemon rind and juice. Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Chill for easier handling. Shape by teaspoon into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Snip balls in half, 3/4 way through, using lightly floured scissors.
Snip each half into thirds.
Lay the 6 petals down on sheet.
Decorate centers with candied cherry halves. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Crush wafers with rolling pin.
Add milk and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack hard in a square pan and put in refrigerator until needed.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each of 12 foil cups.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla flavor and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well.
Add mixture equally to each foil cup.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Chill for 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Top with jelly or preserves or your own fruit choice.

title: zesty potato salad
directions: Combine dry milk, water, mustard, salt and pepper in a small bowl until well mixed. Combine potatoes, green beans, bell pepper and onions in a large bowl. Add milk dressing from small bowl and toss well to coat. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: quick spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Mix salt and pepper with meat; brown and drain.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Break uncooked spaghetti into 3 pieces and scatter over top of boiling meat and vegetable mixture.
Add Worcestershire sauce and 2 teaspoons salt to tomatoes; pour over spaghetti.
Press spaghetti under liquid.
Cover skillet and bring to a boil, then turn heat to low to keep mixture simmering.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: christmas jello
directions: Make lemon jello according to directions.
Add green food coloring and pineapple.
Let sit in refrigerator until congealed. Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread this mixture over green jello.
Make strawberry jello according to directions.
Let it cool and add strawberries.
Let it partially congeal.
Then pour it over the cream cheese layer and chill until you serve it.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar and set aside in small bowl. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form, then add sugar and beat approximately 5 to 6 minutes until stiff peaks form. Add vanilla and salt.
Beat for one minute.
Gently fold in flour/sugar mixture, 1/4 cup at a time.
Bake in ungreased angel food cake pan at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Invert pan and turn cake upside down for 1 1/2 hours, then use knife to cut around edges of pan.
Invert onto plate upside down.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease a 2 quart dish.
Place sliced apples in dish with water.
Add spices and salt.
In bowl, mix flour, sugars and butter until crumbly.
Put mixture on top of apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are soft.
Tastes great with vanilla ice cream!

title: crumb topping for cake or pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with fork or hands.
Makes enough topping for 11 x 17 inch pan.

title: pickled vegetables
directions: Bring to a boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pack vegetables in jars tightly.
Lay sprigs of dill on top of vegetable.
Pour boiling mixture over vegetables.
Seal and let set for 2 weeks.

title: apricot balls
directions: Cook all ingredients, except nut meats in double boiler for 30 minutes, stirring often.
Add nut meats.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Cool.
Form into small rolls or balls and roll in powdered sugar.
If first sugar is absorbed too much, sift more sugar over the balls later.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix well (scald, if you wish).
Chill for several hours in 5-quart home freezer barrel.
When ready to freeze, fill to fill line with whole milk .
Add a few drops of yellow food color for eye appeal.
Freeze and enjoy winter or summer.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onion in butter in electric skillet for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and saute 5+ more minutes.
Add flour and seasonings.
Stir in sour cream.
Be sure to cook on low at least 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving sizes.
In a small bowl, combine flour, salt and black pepper.
Coat meat with seasoned flour.

title: beer burgers
directions: Mix together all but beer and dressing.
Make 6 patties. Broil, fry or barbecue.
Baste with 1/4 cup beer mixed with 1/4 cup French dressing.

title: hot ham dip
directions: Mix all together. Bake until creamy and hot. Serve with crackers or toast.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Blend Bisquick, cheese, salt and pepper; add eggs.
Add grated zucchini to the mixture.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat and add zucchini mixture.
Fry 3 minutes on each side.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 to 10 fritters.

title: bean soup(easy and good)
directions: Cook onion and garlic in Dutch oven in oil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add tomato.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add broth, water, basil, oregano and celery.
Boil. Then reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Add beans, macaroni and pepper.
Boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Stir.
Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: excellent easy roast
directions: Place roast in pan.
Add onion soup and mushroom soup.
Add the potatoes, carrots and celery the last hour.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix soups and rice in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place chicken pieces on top. Sprinkle dry onion soup on top. Drizzle melted butter over dry soup. Sprinkle parsley and paprika over top. Cover tightly with foil and bake for 2 hours.

title: chocolate "philly" fudge
directions: Gradually add powdered sugar to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended with electric mixer.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Press on buttered plate. Sets up very quickly, but stays soft and creamy.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and margarine; add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, egg, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour in greased cake pan. Top with the 3/4 cup topping; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread(yields 3 loaves)
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix together flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg, then add to the zucchini mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Then add the walnuts and raisins.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients; add the milk gradually, then the egg, well beaten, and the melted butter.
Bake in a hot oven in buttered gem pans for 25 minutes.
Basis for one pan of 8 muffins.

title: potato skins
directions: Punch holes in potatoes with fork and coat with thin layer of shortening.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until done.
Cut potatoes lengthwise and scoop insides out.
Insides can be saved and used at a later date.
Brush with melted margarine on insides of potatoes after they have been placed on cookie sheet. Place in oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and fill with cooked bacon that has been crumbled.
Mix the 2 cheeses, add to bacon in potato and return to oven until cheese is melted.
Salt and pepper to taste; sour cream can be added if desired.
Serve warm.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Mix tomatoes, bread crumbs and sugar.
Pour into a slightly buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 375° oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: crisp bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumber, onion, green pepper and whole garlic cloves; add salt.
Cover with crushed ice.
Mix thoroughly. Let stand for 3 hours; drain well.
Remove garlic.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumber mixture.
Bring to boil.
Fill hot jars.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Beat egg; add milk.
Stir in dry ingredients; add melted butter.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, vanilla pudding, oil, water, vanilla and eggs.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; pour butter and brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple and cherries atop sugar.
Pour cake batter over cherries and pineapple.
Bake at 350° just until cake rises; then lower to 300° to get even browning.

title: turkey quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Mix cheese with flour and bouillon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Top with French fried onions during last 5 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: play dough
directions: Mix in a pan over medium heat until the mixture starts clinging into a ball.
Knead until smooth.
Store in a Ziploc or airtight container.

title: apple cake
directions: Place apples with juice in 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and vanilla. Spread dry cake mix evenly over apples. Grate frozen butter evenly over top of cake mix. Sprinkle pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Heat cheese in the soup and add gelatin; cool.
Add rest of ingredients and a pinch of salt and pepper.
Mix in the shrimp; put into a mold and chill.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; press over bottom and 1-inch up the sides to form crust. Seal perforations.
Bake for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: 1-2-3 meat loaf
directions: Mix in a large bowl the ground beef, onion soup and evaporated milk.
With hands wet, shape mixture into loaf.
Place in shallow ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jan's lentils
directions: In a saucepan, place lentils with enough water to cover, plus 1 cup.
Add raw celery.
Add chicken bouillon cubes and bring to a boil.
Add hot sauce, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cook 10 minutes or until firm.
Do not overcook! Add water if needed.

title: potato onion cheddar soup
directions: Cook garlic, onion, celery and potatoes in oil for 10 minutes; stir often.
Add broth, carrot, salt and pepper.
Boil; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in milk; heat through.
Add cheese and parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: red salmon loaf
directions: Mix in bowl: red salmon, chopped onion, beaten eggs, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Butter a loaf pan.
Cook 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: children's punch
directions: Mix all 4 ingredients together and serve over crushed ice.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place a slice of cheese on each piece of chicken. Mix soup and wine. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle herb stuffing over chicken, soup, etc.
Drizzle melted margarine on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: marmalade drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Blend in the dry ingredients and the marmalade.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Mix lemon juice, olive oil and water.
Taste, if too lemony add more water.
Place thighs in 10 x 12-inch pan. Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle oregano over thighs, turn and do other side.
Very carefully add lemon mixture to chicken having it about 1/2 inch over chicken; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Make Lemon Potatoes for vegetable.

title: summer delight
directions: You will need a juicer.

title: chicken pie
directions: After chicken meat has been deboned, combine all vegetables, soup, meat, chicken broth and milk into large mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Roll out one layer of crust very thin with a rolling pin and then place into an 8 x 8 square pan or a pie pan.
Continue by pouring filling mixture on top of crust and then roll top layer before placing it on top of filling.
Be sure to cut slits in top dough before baking at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: garlic dill pickles
directions: Chunk pickles to neck of jar.
Add dill and garlic. Heat other ingredients and fill cans.
Put in hot water bath and cold pack only until boiling point, then remove immediately from water. They are ready in 2 weeks.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, soft butter and egg.
Sift together 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mix and milk (alternating).
Fold in blueberries.
Mix together with pastry blender the sugar, flour, and butter until coarse.
Sprinkle on top of batter and bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 to 60 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients, chocolate chips and vanilla. Bake in ungreased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple with pistachio pudding mix.
Stir by hand.
Add to other ingredients and pour into covered bowl.
Chill in refrigerator for about 6 hours before serving.

title: chicken salad souffl
directions: Put 1/2 of the cubed bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine chicken, onion, green pepper, celery, mayonnaise and seasoning and arrange this mix over the bread cubes.
Cover with balance of bread cubes.
Beat eggs; add milk and pour over all.
Cover and chill overnight (or for at least several hours) in refrigerator.
Spoon the mushroom soup over top and bake uncovered in 325° oven about 1 hour.	Sprinkle cheese over the top for the last few minutes of baking.

title: halupkes(cabbage rolls)
directions: Parboil 2 cabbages, after removing core, until most outer leaves are soft.

title: directions for alfalfa tea
directions: Boil slowly for 15 minutes and strain in quart receptacle.
If needed add sufficient water to make a quart of tea. Keep in refrigerator. It may be sweetened as desired.

title: steamed potatoes with cabbage
directions: Place the potatoes in a steamer basket over simmering water. Arrange the cabbage wedges in a single layer over the potatoes. Cover and steam until the potatoes and cabbage are tender, about 25 minutes. While the vegetables are steaming, toast the caraway seeds in a small skillet sprayed with nonstick spray over medium heat, stirring until seeds turn light brown and fragrant, 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Stir the seeds, onion, garlic and salt into the yogurt until blended. Divide the steamed vegetables among serving dishes and spoon over the caraway yogurt. Serves 4.

title: sugar-free trifle cake
directions: After cake is baked and cooled, slice or split into 2 layers. Place one layer in a large bowl.
Add 1/2 of the strawberries on top of the cake layer.
Put 1/2 of the pudding over the berries, then add a layer of Cool Whip.
Put second layer of cake on next; continue the same procedure.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potato chips, adding almonds last.
Pour into an 8 x 5-inch oiled casserole dish. Sprinkle top with potato chips and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and flour together. Add rhubarb and mix well. Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 1 hour. 8 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° until warmed through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Beat thoroughly the ground steak, eggs, bread crumbs, ketchup, Accent, warm water and Lipton onion soup mix.
Put into loaf pan. Cover with two strips of bacon, if you like that flavor.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Separate cabbage leaves and place in boiling water until pliable.
Mix all ingredients, except cabbage, tomato sauce and water, in mixing bowl.
Fill each cabbage leaf with some of the meat mixture and roll up.
Place in baking dish.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves about 4.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients together in double boiler until thick; add butter and melt thoroughly.
Take off fire and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Cover with meringue made from 2 egg whites, beaten thoroughly with 4 teaspoons sugar added. Cook slowly until brown.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken breasts in egg, then into bread crumbs.
Heat oil in electric skillet to 360°. Brown chicken on both sides and remove to casserole dish.
Stir tomato sauce and herbs in a pan.
Heat until boiling, simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover top with Mozzarella.
Bake 10 minutes more uncovered.

title: crunchy peanut butter bars
directions: In large mixing bowl cream shortening with sugar until light and creamy.
Beat in egg.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Blend well.
Stir in peanut butter chips, fruit, coconut and almonds.
Spread into greased 16 x 11 inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile in small saucepan melt butter with milk over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar until creamy. Drizzle over warm cookies.
Cut into 2 x 1 inch bars.
Garnish each with halved cherry.
When cool, wrap each bar in plastic wrap for mailing or giving.
This kitchen-tested recipe makes 70 bars.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Melt butter in a 13x9-inch baking pan, sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour milk evenly over crumbs, top with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly with fork. Bake for 25 minutes or until lightly browned, cool, cut into squares.

title: fruit fluff
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice together.
Drain the fruit and mix it with the milk mixture.
Pour the mixture into 3 graham cracker crusts, then let chill.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: In a glass serving bowl, combine pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Fold in pudding mix, blending well.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Garnish with pecans or maraschino cherries, if desired.
(I chopped up about 6 cherries and blended them in instead of using as topping, makes it look better.)
Makes about 6 servings.

title: kolaches(no-knead dough)
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine; cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, egg and half the flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover tightly with waxed paper and refrigerate dough at least 2 hours.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator up to 3 days.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts; cool and cut into bite size pieces.
In greased casserole, layer chicken, thawed broccoli and several slices of cheese.
Pour over the can of soup, undiluted.
Have your Stove Top dressing made and put on top.
Cook 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: oreo cake
directions: Mix ice cream, Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
In an oblong cake pan, pour 1/2 crushed Oreos on the bottom of pan.
Pour in ice cream mixture and top with rest of Oreos.

title: potato-meat scallop
directions: Alternately layer potatoes, onions and meat in casserole dish. Continue until all is used.
Salt and pepper.
Pour soup and water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dilly grilled turkey
directions: This recipe calls for half of a fresh or frozen turkey breast.
If your market carries only whole turkey breast, ask the butcher to cut one in half for you.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Fry meats and drain. Add spices and cheese until melted. Spread on rye. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. These freeze well.

title: confetti rice
directions: Cook rice; follow directions on bag.
Saute peppers and onion in small amount of olive oil.
Add to chopped tomato.
Toss with mushrooms, including juice.
Add cooked rice; toss.
Put in casserole dish; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake until hot at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in a square casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken cilantro (pollo al cilantro)
directions: Cook onion and garlic in butter and oil.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until done.
Stir in cilantro.

title: broccoli blankets
directions: Top ham with cheese. Place broccoli spear in center. Roll up. Secure with toothpicks. Place in 6x10 baking dish. Cook onions in butter until tender. Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually pour over ham. Bake 350 degrees 25 minutes.

title: yooper fish chowder
directions: In a 6 to 8-quart kettle, melt 1/4 cup butter over medium heat. Saute onions until tender but not brown.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper and water. Top with fish and simmer 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in scalded milk, evaporated milk and the rest of the butter.
Heat but don't boil. Add more salt and pepper, if desired.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat on medium-low chili with beans and 1/2 jar of the salsa until it thickens.
Once that is thickened, pour the contents into a flat, glass dish, either oblong or an old glass pie dish.
Add other ingredients:
first sour cream, then sprinkle lettuce, cheese, tomatoes, onion and black olives over the top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together; pour into buttered dish.

title: spicy turkey chili
directions: Fry turkey burger and onions until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Reduce heat, simmer, stirring occasionally until thick, 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: cranberry nut pastry
directions: Bring concentrate to a boil; add cranberries and dates.
Cover and cook until moist and thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Add honey. Remove from heat and stir in nuts.
Cool completely.
Roll dough into a rectangle 20 x 6-inches, 1/2 inch thick.
Spread filling over center third of dough lengthwise.
On each long side, cut 1-inch slices, 2 inches long.
Starting at one end, fold strips at an angle across filling, alternating from side to side.
Place bread on oiled cookie sheet.
Gently brush top of bread with 2 tablespoons apple juice concentrate.
Cover; let rise in warm place until almost doubled.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Serves 24.

title: cucumber casserole
directions: Cook ground meat in butter until brown. Add onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic; cook until tender. Add bread crumbs and egg; cook another 5 minutes. Add chopped cucumbers. Top with bread crumbs and bake at 300° about 20 minutes.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Brown hot sausage and onion.
Drain.
Mix meal, baking powder, salt, milk, eggs, creamed corn and salad oil.
In greased pan, pour meal mix.
Top with sausage and onion.
Top with 2 cups grated Cheddar cheese.
Pour rest of batter on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 425°.
Cool for 10 minutes and serve in squares.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve hot water and Jell-O.
Add blueberries and pineapple. Let congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla. Beat smooth.
Spread over salad.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup pecans.

title: jean's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
Have baked pie shell ready.
Beat whites very stiff and add 3 tablespoons sugar; brown.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, milk, onion, cornflakes and salt and pepper all together.
Form into patties.
Roll in flour and brown in fat.
Place patties in baking dish.
Cover with mushroom soup and 1 1/2 cups water.
Bake at 310° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, mixing well after each addition. Sift flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Mix in vanilla.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove to wire rack to cool. May bake in 3 layers if preferred.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: baba ghannouj
directions: Grill eggplant over a charcoal fire for 30 to 40 minutes, turning frequently.
Alternatively place on center shelf in a hot oven and cook until soft, again turning often.

title: nancy mcginn's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter.
Add spices, clams and chopped stems.
Add wine. Simmer 10 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add bread crumbs to desired consistency, then add cheese.
Stuff mixture into mushroom caps. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coriander peanuts
directions: Cut the coriander to small pieces.
Mix the peanuts with the coriander chips.
Add salt.
Then add soy sauce.
Finally add sesame oil.
Mix well and is ready to be served.

title: cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage; add water, tomatoes, onion, sausage, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a mixer.
Spread on tortilla shells and roll tightly. Chill 2 hours. Cut into 1-inch pieces and hold with toothpicks.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions, using a greased and floured oblong pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
While cake is warm, punch holes in top with fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Sprinkle coconut over milk.
Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over top of cake and sprinkle last package of coconut over Cool Whip.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: english muffin hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread mixture on Thomas English muffins and broil until mixture melts.
Cut each muffin into 4 pieces and serve hot.

title: taco salad
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Simmer meat until brown.
Add hot sauce and cheese to meat and stir well.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes and onions; toss.
Just before serving, add meat and cheese mixture and toss.
Add corn chips and toss again.
Serve immediately.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Fry onion.
Add hamburger; cook and drain.
Add mustard, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Add water.
Cook until it comes to a boil, then serve.

title: pate maison
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes; strain. Add livers to liquid.
Cook below simmering 10 minutes.
Drain. Pass through blender.
Blend remaining ingredients with liver. Stir in brandy.
Line 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with foil.
Pack pate into pan.
Chill.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix together all ingredients; blend well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased pan.

title: antipasta salad
directions: Boil spirals.
Rinse when done.
Prepare 1 or 2 packages of Good Seasons Italian dressing as directed on package.
Pour over pasta.
Cut up meats and cheeses into cubes.
Chop vegetables and add to salad.
Chill.
Use your own discretion as to the amount of meats and cheese (1/2 to 3/4 pound of each).

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Blend together pudding mix, sugar and water.
Cook over low hear until all sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Serve warm over ice cream, cake or brownies.
Store in refrigerator and reheat in microwave as needed. Use sugar free pudding mix for a low carb treat.

title: orange jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Let set in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.

title: old fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes and reduce heat to 375° for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: *Self-rising flour may be used, omitting salt and soda.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook meat pieces until all the water that cooks out of it evaporates.
Add all the vegetables and stir-fry until transparent.
Wrap small amount in egg roll wrappers and deep fry. Serve with sweet and sour sauce and fried rice and almonds (Rice-A-Roni brand).

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and chocolate. Blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Add nuts.
Drop from teaspoon 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 10 to 12 minutes.
While warm, frost.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: bed & breakfast gourmet brownies
directions: Melt 3 squares chocolate with shortening over warm water; cool slightly. Blend together eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt; stir in chocolate mixture, then flour. Fold in walnuts. Turn into well-greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes. Spoon preserves over hot brownies; spread carefully. Let cool. Spread Velvet Chocolate Glaze over brownies.

title: banana cake
directions: Put bananas and shortening in a mixing bowl with 2 tablespoons sour milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Add 1 tablespoon sour milk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Nutmeats may be added, if desired.

title: seafood pasta primavera
directions: While penne pasta is cooking, add onions and carrots to olive oil. Cook until tender. Add broccoli and squash and cook until tender. Add seafood to mixture and cook until done (another 3-4 minutes). Add seasonings to mixture. Serve on top of pasta. Add additional olive oil and toss.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Toss sliced apples in sugar mixture and turn into pie shell.
Combine oats, brown sugar, pecans, cinnamon and melted butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake about 40 minutes or until topping is brown and apples are tender.

title: eggs portugal
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the cheese, mustard, sausage and bread; pour in dish.
Add the milk and eggs just before baking.
(May be assembled the night before, except for milk and eggs.)

title: crock-pot brisket
directions: Season brisket according to taste.
Set crock-pot on high and put in the brisket and pour barbecue sauce over it.
Cook on high for 4 1/2 hours or until desired tenderness.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Take a 1 1/2 or 2-quart pot and melt butter in it.
Add Karo and sugar.
Cook at medium heat until it comes to a boil while stirring the whole time.
Take off heat and add peanut butter, stir until completely melted.
Have your corn flakes in another large bowl, then pour your heated mixture over them.
Drop by spoon onto wax or aluminum foil.
Let cool, then eat.
I usually make a double batch.
The kids love this.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Do not wait for cake to pull away from pan.
It will be dry.
This cake will be very moist.
Top with your buttercream icing or chopped nuts.
Put chopped nuts on before baking.

title: sour cream and cheddar chip dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours in the refrigerator and serve with potato chips or small crackers.

title: fruit tea(note:  should be made under adult supervision.)
directions: Fill a kettle with at least 6 cups of cold tap water.
Place the pot on the stove and bring the water to a boil over medium-high heat.
Place the orange on a cutting board and cut it into 4 pieces.
Remove as many seeds as possible and put 2 of the quarters in the pot, reserving the remaining 2.
Repeat process with the lemon.
Add the tea bag, cinnamon stick and clove to the teapot.
When the water in the kettle reaches boil, pour the heated water into the pot; cover and let the mixture steep for 3 minutes.
Remove the cover and with a wooden spoon, press down on the fruit quarters.
Stir the tea well, then remove the bag and other ingredients.
Carefully fill 4 tea cups with the tea.
Serve with honey and extra orange and lemon.
Let friends sweeten and flavor their own tea.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate chicken for 2 to 3 hours or more.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on size and amount of chicken.

title: goulash
directions: Fry the hamburger with chopped onion, bell pepper and celery; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, dump the applesauce.
Spread it to cover bottom of pan.
Dump pineapple over top of the applesauce; spread.
Next, dump the white cake mix; spread evenly.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Spread so that it covers all of the cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake in oven for about 35 to 45 minutes, or until top is lightly browned.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in small amount of water.
Simmer until tender; drain.
Saute onion in small amount of margarine.
Add all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy stew
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Drain.
Add potatoes, pepper, onion and seasonings.
Add water and let simmer, covered, until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: scallops st. jacques
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place scallops (whole) in saucepan. Pour wine over and cook for 5 minutes.
Drain scallops, saving wine liquid for later.
Put in an ovenproof dish.

title: italian potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the potatoes, celery, cheese, pepper, salami, onion and pepperoni.
Then add sour cream to potato mixture and toss lightly to blend.
Fold in the tomatoes. Cover and chill.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Add
water and salt.
Cook potatoes until tender;
about 25 minutes.
Drain.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper,
sweet
pickles
and pickles and juice, mustard, celery, onions and eggs.
Add to potatoes and mix thoroughly.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain well.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix this and broccoli in a greased casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes in moderate oven (350°).

title: french loaf
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper; add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste. Drain meat and add Cheez Whiz.

title: hearty sausage and vegetable pot(a hearty one-dish dinner)
directions: Brown bacon in 4-quart saucepan.
Add onion and celery and cook several minutes.
Stir in sausage, water, parsley, peppercorns and salt.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add carrots, parsnips, rutabaga and potatoes.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Arrange cabbage wedges over top, cover and cook until cabbage is tender, about 15 minutes. Lightly season cabbage with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle top with minced fresh parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon poppy seed cake(low-fat)
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar.
Add oil and next 4 ingredients. Beat at medium speed for 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour into a 10-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Beat lightly together the sugar, eggs and shortening.
Mix together and add the flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add and mix in the milk and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: paul harvey wild rice soup
directions: Rinse and cook rice for 40 to 60 minutes.
Saute onion and butter until tender.
Add water, milk and soup.
Add cheese and rice.
Simmer until creamy.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix all together, except cooked and deboned chicken.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: salad by candlelight
directions: On small plate, place lettuce.
Place pineapple ring in center of leaves.
Put 1/2 banana in hole of each.
Attach cherry half on top of each banana to represent a flame.
Now doesn't that look like a candle.

title: strawberry citrus punch(easy holiday punch)
directions: In order to make it possible for everyone to attend church next week we are planning a special no-excuse Sunday.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until they are 1/2 cooked.
Fry Spam.
Add all ingredients into a large pot or crock-pot.
Include water.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Lightly sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt.
Brown in butter in Dutch oven.
Add sherry and liquid from can of mushrooms.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to serving dish.
Measure pan juices and add water to make 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Blend liquid and chicken gravy mix in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring continuously.
Blend in sour cream and add mushrooms.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: microwave barbecue chicken
directions: Combine chili sauce, honey and onion.
Place chicken on microwave baking dish; cover with sauce and cook at full power for 10 minutes.
Add green pepper and cook at full power 2 more minutes.

title: buttermilk yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add the warm buttermilk, egg and the shortening.
In a medium bowl, sift all the dry ingredients (except the flour) together.
Add the yeast mixture, then add enough flour to make the dough easy to handle.
Knead until smooth.

title: ham and cheese frittata(like quiche; serves 4)
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute mushrooms, pepper and onions until tender.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs and water until foamy.
Add egg mixture and ham to skillet.
Pour into greased pie pan after mixing thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until eggs are solid.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese and allow cheese to melt.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in bite size pieces; do not chop or grind.
Add mayonnaise, rice vinegar, onion and raisins.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add crumbled bacon and shelled sunflower seeds.
Mix well and serve.

title: antipasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together except dressing.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Just prior to serving toss the ingredients with dressing.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Put first 2 ingredients in blender.
Add remaining ingredients. Make into ball.
Spread cocktail sauce over.
Best made the night before.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with evaporated milk in microwave.
Combine cake mix, water, butter and eggs.

Blend on low speed for 2 minutes. Pour half the batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cake puffs up and is gooey. Pour melted caramels over partially baked layer to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Sprinkle chips and pecans over caramels.
Pour remaining batter over all and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when touched (may take 40 minutes).
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.
Ice, if desired (creamy fudge).

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix well, chill and enjoy.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars.
Stir in egg, peanut butter and remaining ingredients.
Bake 10 minutes in 300° to 350° oven.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes, until set.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, onion and peas.
Spread mayonnaise over the peas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover airtight and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, add croutons and toss well.
Garnish with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: sour cream rhubarb cake
directions: Mix white sugar, melted margarine, nuts and cinnamon and set aside.
Cream together brown sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Add together along with sour cream.
Fold in rhubarb.
Turn into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: never fail brownies
directions: Cream butter with sugar; beat in eggs.
Blend in melted cocoa and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: henry's oatmeal cookies
directions: *Add quantities to your liking.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done. Save 1 cup chicken broth. Cook spaghetti in remaining chicken broth. Cut chicken into small pieces and mix with cream of mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, chicken broth and spaghetti. Cut Velveeta cheese into smaller pieces and mix into spaghetti mixture. Cover top with cheese slices and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Makes large dish.

title: won't be nothing left cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Cool.

title: microwave rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Cover. Microwave on High for 5 minutes. Reduce power to Medium. Microwave 10 to 13 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Fluff with fork before serving.

title: texas tamale dinner
directions: Brown beef in skillet; add onion and cook until onion is soft. Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, corn, one teaspoon salt, granulated garlic and chili powder.
Cover; simmer over medium-low heat for 15 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with sliced olives.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice until blended.
Pour in crusts and refrigerate.

title: chocolate milk cooler
directions: Place milk, milk powder, cocoa, vanilla and sugar in blender. Cover and blend at high speed until smooth.
Remove center of cover and add ice, one at a time, blending until each is thoroughly crushed.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion, bacon and add remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.
(Browned sausage or ground beef may also be added.)

title: supper dish
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Cook celery in water, save water.
Add rice, soy sauce and celery water to meat mixture.
Mix in both cans of soup.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole lined with Chinese noodles. Add remaining noodles to top of meat mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Do not add salt.

title: parmesan mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender. Drain. Add garlic, cheese, cream, salt and pepper. Mash potatoes until smooth.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse with cold water until cool.
Add vegetables and mix well.
Combine milk, vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add to macaroni mixture.
Mix well.
Chill for 4 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix eggs and cottage cheese.
Add to this the broccoli.
Mix melted oleo and cornbread mix.
Blend all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; add juice and mix well.
Thirty minutes before serving, add ginger ale and club soda.
Serves 25.

title: party mints
directions: Gradually add cream cheese to sugar.
Add food coloring and peppermint.
The mixture will be very stiff.
Form into balls and place on waxed paper.
Flatten each ball with bottom of a glass. Dust with sugar, if desired.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch (preferably Corning Ware) pan.
Layer bread slices (packed tightly together), Mozzarella or Swiss cheese, meat, mushrooms (optional) and Cheddar cheese.

title: crab casserole
directions: Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and spices.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Add nuts.
Alternately beat dry ingredients and applesauce until smooth.
Pour into loaf pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: do-nuts
directions: Put shortening, sugar and salt into a bowl. Stir in boiling water.
Add milk.
Cool to warm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup
warm water and add sugar.
Stir in egg and 2 cups flour.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cream cheese with mixer.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in foil.
Keep refrigerated.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake well before using.

title: stegosaurus salad
directions: Mix together twigs (pretzels), leaves (lettuce), grass (sprouts), hot lava (salad dressing).
Eat and keep an eye out for Tyrannosaurus Rex.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Put nuts in bottom of greased (I use Joy spray) and floured Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and put in pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Saut the onions in margarine until soft. Combine all the ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°. In bowl, stir together graham cracker crumbs, sugar, cocoa and butter. Press mixture on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. In large bowl, beat softened cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in condensed milk, then melted peanut butter chips until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Stir in mini chocolate chips. Pour over crust. Bake 55 to 65 minutes, until set. Remove and cool completely. Remove from pan. Garnish with Chocolate Drizzle. Refrigerate.

title: shrimp oriental
directions: Peel and clean shrimp.
Mince garlic and black beans.
Combine oyster sauce, Korean sauce, chicken bouillon, garlic and black beans in bowl.
Add shrimp and marinate in refrigerator for about 2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour gradually to which salt and soda have been added. Add bananas and vanilla; beat well.
Add nuts, beating well. Pour in 4 greased and floured coffee tin cans (1 pound tins). Pour about 1/2 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small sauce pan; cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture boils. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla; stir until blended.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate beef or chicken several hours or overnight.
Brush with honey.
Broil couple of minutes on each side.
Burn them a little bit.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Saute hamburger meat, pepper and onion.
Cook until done. Place hamburger mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 cheese.
Add mushroom soup.
Cover with 2 cups creamed Irish potatoes and other 1/2 of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Mix meat and bread crumbs.
Make into patties.
Fry.
Combine all ingredients and simmer until celery is tender.
Add patties and simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: cream-filled mini cakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl and beat until well blended.
Add chocolate chips; mix well and set aside.
Prepare cake mix using package directions.
Fill paper-lined miniature muffin cups 2/3 full.
Drop 1 teaspoon cheese mixture into each cup.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 15 minutes or until tests done.

title: gelatin orange dessert
directions: Soften gelatin in water and stir in Sweet & Low, salt and hot water until gel is dissolved.
Stir in orange juice.
Pour 3/4 cup into each mold.
Keep in ice box until it sets.
2 servings.

title: joggin in a jug
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Drink 2 ounces a day for high cholesterol.

title: wine recipe
directions: Squeeze berries or grapes into a mush and tie up in a stone jar so insects can't get to it.
Let stand for 10 days or until grapes ferment good.
Strain and sweeten using 3 measurings of juice and one of sugar.
Let stand and ferment again.
Skim every morning until skim quits rising.
Bottle but don't cork tight for 4 or 5 days.
Use three cups juice to 1 cup sugar.

title: lemon dijon chicken
directions: Combine breadcrumbs and lemon rind, stirring well.
Combine lemon juice, mustard and lime juice; brush mixture over both sides of chicken.
Dredge chicken in breadcrumbs.
Place chicken in baking dish coated with pan coating.
Sprinkle with remaining breadcrumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn over and bake an additional 15 minutes. Garnish with remaining lemon slices if desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend pudding mix with milk.
Add sour cream and blend until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer mixture with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Make sure it is topped with pudding mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves approximately 12.

title: hamburger-cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add meat, salt and pepper, heating through, but not browning.
Spread 1/2 of cabbage in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with meat mixture and rice.
Top with remaining cabbage.
Pour soup over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pot roast
directions: Season roast with salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Place in pot or iron skillet.
Let brown on both sides.
Pour a cup or two of water over the roast.
Cook on top of the stove or in the oven. As the water boils out, pour more water in for your gravy.
Use a slow fire if cooked on top of stove.

title: eclair cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan put one layer graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Add 2 layers of crackers on top of pudding.
Pour remaining pudding over crackers.
Add one layer of crackers.
Mix cocoa, oil, vanilla, butter, sugar and milk. Spread over last cracker layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Cut into cubes.
In a clear bowl place 1/2 the cake cubes; cover with 1 can cherry pie filling, half the pudding, half the pineapple and half the bananas.
Top with half the Cool Whip.
Repeat for second layer.
Garnish with pecans, cherries and coconut.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: crispy enchilada casserole
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups grated cheese, enchilada sauce, chili, tomato paste, water, onion and corn chips, reserving 1 cup.
Pour into lightly greased, oblong baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spread sour cream over top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Put remaining corn chips around edge and bake 5 more minutes.

title: candied apples
directions: Cook all ingredients except apples until the temperature reaches 290°.
Do not stir.
Add several drops of red food coloring.
Place pan in hot water to keep from hardening.
Begin dipping apples at once.
Cool on greased surface.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use teaspoon to one cup hot water.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the broccoli, bacon, onion and raisins.
Separate bowl.
Make dressing of 1 cup mayonnaise, 1 tablespoon vinegar and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix the dressing over broccoli mixture and toss. Serve.

title: busy day chicken and dressing
directions: Melt margarine; stir in water.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch baking dish with margarine and put 1/2 stuffing mix in it.
Add to the chicken pieces celery, onion, salt and mayonnaise, mixing well. Make a layer of chicken on top of stuffing, then another layer of stuffing.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over dish.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cooking oil and blend. Add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk, figs and pecans. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a 12 x 9 x 2 pan.

title: creamy chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice into a greased 13 by 9 inch pan.
In a saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat; add chicken, cheese and sour cream; stir until the cheese is melted. Pour over rice.
Melt the remaining butter then toss with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 10-15 minutes or until heated through.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In a large bowl, combine the vinegar with the water, red wine, onions, orange, garlic, bay leaf, salt, cloves, peppercorns and ground pepper.
Stir the marinade well.
Add the beef and refrigerate it for 4 to 5 days, stirring it once a day.
Remove the meat and drain it thoroughly.
Brown on all sides in a little heated butter or oil.
Add the marinade, strained of all but the onion slices and 1/4 cup tomato puree.
Simmer the meat for about 2 hours or until it is tender.

title: chocolate chip kentucky bluegrass pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour filling into unbaked 10-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until pie is set.
Yield: one pie.

title: black olive and cream cheese mix
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature. Stir in enough mayonnaise to make mixture creamy and spreadable. Fold in black olives and pecans. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: lime marshmallow salad
directions: Add gelatin to water,
mixing well. Add marshmallows and stir until melted. Add cream
cheese
and
mix
well.
Place in refrigerator until slightly
congealed.
Then
add
mayonnaise, pineapple and 1/2 cup nuts,
beating
with electric mixer until well blended.
Place in refrigerator until congealed.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top of salad.

title: super pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in hot oil; add garlic and cook for 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce, salt, water and vegetables.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch that has been blended with tomato juice.
Add tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix ingredients well and shape into log.
Roll in paprika. Chill and slice.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Bake chicken breasts on a cookie sheet until done; cool and skin.
Shred and chop.
Mix in bowl the chicken, cream of chicken soup, milk, onion and green chili salsa.
Grease a baking dish. In layers, add the tortilla strips, Cheddar cheese, chili salsa and chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter, vanilla and 1 egg.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a boil; boil for 1 minute. Add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: oyster stew
directions: Cook oysters in water; boil until done.
Add to milk and salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make meatballs out of ground beef; fry and drain fat off.
In small saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce, 1/2 cup water and salt.
Cook until thick.
Add meatballs and pineapple chunks, green peppers, onion and water chestnuts.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over rice with soy sauce.

title: honey bear brownies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar in small mixer bowl.
Blend in honey or syrup and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from pan.

title: chocolate candy(don't double recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts. When starts to boil, boil for 3 minutes. Take off of heat. Stir in 1 cup nuts. Drop by spoonful on buttered wax paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Mix cooked broccoli, cheese and 1/2 stick butter in 1-quart casserole. Melt 1/2 stick butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Spoon over broccoli.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: saucy microwave cauliflower
directions: Remove leaves and woody stem from cauliflower.
Rinse clean. Wrap in wax paper.
Puncture paper.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Unwrap.
Place in glass casserole.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over cauliflower.
Microwave, uncovered, for 1 minute.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving 1/2 cup Chow Mein noodles for topping. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and top with rest of Chow Mein noodles. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Saute onions, garlic,
tomato puree, white pepper, salt and oregano in oil for
minutes;
set aside.
Cook lasagne noodles and
lay out
on
a
clean,
lint-free
cloth.
Slice zucchini lengthwise and blanch
in
boiling salted water for 3 minutes. Assemble as follows:
In
a
buttered
roasting pan, layer noodles; then spread layer of Ricotta with spatula.
Add zucchini slices and spread
with
tomato
sauce
until totally covered. Sprinkle with
grated Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Repeat the process
and
cover with light Bechamel sauce, the grated cheeses and
melted butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 40 minutes or
until
golden
brown
on top.
Let lasagna sit for approximately 30 minutes before serving.

title: saucepan raisin bars
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, water, raisins, spices and salt in saucepan.
Heat gently, then boil three minutes.
Let cool.
Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder into cooled mixture; mix together.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drizzle powdered sugar glaze or frost with favorite frosting.
Cut into small squares or slim slices.

title: microwave caramel (sticky) popcorn
directions: While making the batch of popcorn, melt butter and marshmallows on High in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Once melted, stir in brown sugar.
Toss well with the popcorn.
Serve warm.

title: tracy's baked steak
directions: Brown steak in pan.
Pour all ingredients over top of steak. Cover with foil and bake for 2 hours or until tender.

title: seven cup pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Press mixture into clean coffee tins.
(Use the 13 ounce size tins; you will need two.) Cover with aluminum foil.
Steam by placing tins in water approximately halfway up the sides and heat to 300°.
Steam for 3 hours.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat
oven
Combine eggs, milk and seasoning; mix well.
Toss
cheese
with
flour.
Add cheese mixture and bacon to egg mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican hot dish
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery and drain.
Heat soups; add to meat.
Blend well.
Add chillies and sour cream.
Stir to blend well together.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all of these ingredients together and chill.

title: sweet suet soup
directions: Put prunes, rice and about 2 1/2 cups water in pressure cooker and cook for 10 minutes.
Cook much longer in a pan.
In the pan with the prune mixture add some more water, raisins, cinnamon, orange and sugar.
Cook it slow for about 1 hour.
Then add the fruit cocktail and tapioca.
Cook just until dissolved.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cucumber, mixing until well blended.
Stir in cucumbers.
Chill several hours or overnight. Serve with chips or vegetables.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar well.
Beat egg yolks (save whites for meringue).
Add small amount of sugar and flour to egg yolks.
Beat alternately adding sugar, flour and milk to egg mixture.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Grease pan with butter.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture until all mixture is used. Beat egg whites until thick.
Add 1/2 cup sugar for meringue.
Cook at 400° until brown.

title: mo-lassie milk
directions: Mix the milk and molasses together with a whisk or spoon.
Add a dash of ginger or cinnamon.
Serve hot or cold.

title: date-pecan candy
directions: If pecans are fresh, salt and bake them.
Place 1/2 pecan inside pitted date.
Roll in sugar.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Cream the cream cheese until smooth.
