Gradually beat in sugar and blend thoroughly.
Add vanilla and a drop of food coloring. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into ball walnut size and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate several more hours until firm.
Makes 20.

title: good frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk and cook over low heat until thick. Refrigerate until cool (preferably overnight).
Cream together oleo and Crisco 4 minutes.
Add sugar.
Mix 4 minutes.
Add flour/milk mixture and vanilla.
Mix 4 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix in large bowl until well blended.
Fry in deep fat fryer until golden brown.

title: grandmother's roll recipe
directions: Beat water, yeast and egg. Cream the shortening, sugar and salt.
Combine together in a large mixing bowl, gradually adding flour to form a soft ball of dough.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface (dough). Cover and let rise until doubled. Turn out onto lightly floured surface. Roll until flat. Use biscuit cutter to form roll shapes.
Place in greased pans. Cover and let rise until doubled. Bake in hot 400° oven until lightly browned. Brush tops with melted butter.

title: blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan with butter. Blend the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a medium-size bowl with a wooden spoon. In another medium-size bowl, beat the eggs with a whisk until blended. Whisk in the melted butter and the vanilla. Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and pour the wet ingredients. Using the wooden spoon, stir until the mixture is blended. Add the nuts with a few broad strokes. Spread the batter evenly in the prepared pan. Bake the bars on the center oven rack until golden and a tester inserted in the center comes out clean or with moist crumbs, 35 to 40 minutes. Place the pan on a rack to cool for 1 hour before cutting. Makes 9 to 12 bars.

title: broccoli, ham and rice au gratin
directions: Melt the butter in a Dutch oven and saute the onion until tender.
Add the soup, garlic powder and cheese.
Stir until cheese has melted.
Drain the mushrooms and the broccoli and add to the mixture along with the rice and the cooked, diced ham.
Drain the pimentos and gently stir in the mixture.
Spoon into a lightly greased baking dish.
Cover and chill for 8 hours to let the flavors blend.
When ready to bake, remove from refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and scatter crumbled onion rings on top.
Return to oven and bake for 5 to 8 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place all ingredients into casserole.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: chicken pasta
directions: Cook and cube chicken. In big skillet, melt margarine. Saute onion and bell pepper. Add Ro-Tel, soup and 2 cans of water. Cook pasta according to directions; drain. Put back in pot and pour hot ingredients over pasta. Add cubed cheese; mix. Put in sprayed baking dish. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In buttered casserole, place pork chops and cover with layer of zucchini.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover with layer of onion, tomato and green pepper.
Season and repeat layers.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Add cherries (or other fruit) last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until done.
Use 9-inch cake pan, greased.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Cream cocoa and butter together. Add remaining ingredients.

title: grandma's raspberry delight
directions: Boil applesauce.
Add jello and blend.
Add frozen raspberries.
Stir, using a large fork to break raspberries into chunks.
Continue stirring until raspberries are mostly thawed. Chill several hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes. Serve with a plain type of cracker (i.e. Carr's crackers).

title: beer-b-cue sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine. Bring to boil. Cook and stir 5 minutes. Add onion, thinly sliced and 1/2 lemon, thinly sliced. Brush sauce over ribs, burger, chicken, etc.

title: divinity candy
directions: In heavy (2-quart) saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture boils. Cook over medium heat (candy thermometer reaches 250, hard boil stage), without stirring and bubbling over entire surface.
As temperature nears 250, beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Gradually pour hot syrup in thin stream over egg whites, beating at high speed; beat 4-5 minutes more until mixture holds its shape.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or spread in buttered 10x6 inch dish.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen pieces.
May add candied cherries or chopped nuts after 5 minutes beating time.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Melt butter. Add flour, salt and pepper; stir to make paste. Add broth and milk.
Boil 1 minute.
Add peas, carrots and chicken.
Line casserole dish with 1/2 of the sliced biscuits. Pour filling mixture over biscuits and place remaining half of sliced biscuits on top. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown
beef;
drain
well;
add sauce, onions and chili powder,
mix
well
and bring to a slow boil.
Add beans; stir well.
Pour
1/2 of mixture into casserole dish, spread 1/2 of cheese on, pour remaining meat
mixture
on,
then the rest of the cheese.
Top with can of
biscuits and put a pat of margarine on each one.
Bake
at
until
biscuits
are golden brown.

title: cottage cheese delight
directions: Lightly mix cheese, nuts, grapes and mayonnaise.
Add salt to taste.
Garnish with cluster of grapes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix jello and Cool Whip. Add drained orange sections and mix well. Add marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.

title: white punch
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and freeze to a "slush" consistency. When ready to serve, put "slush" into punch bowl and add the Sprite. Be sure to have the Sprite very cold before adding to the mixture.

title: cowboy dinner
directions: Brown hamburger.
Place in casserole baking dish.
Slice potatoes and onion on top of meat.
Slice layer of carrots over potatoes.
Top with tomatoes.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: charlotte's chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done; take chicken out. Add 16 ounces spaghetti noodles in boiling water used for cooking chicken; debone chicken.

Saut onions in butter. When spaghetti is done, add deboned chicken, sauteed onions, can of Ro-Tel tomatoes, mushroom soup, chicken soup, chopped up Velveeta cheese and one can of water. Mix together and bake in a 9 x 13 pan until cheese is melted.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper.
Pour off drippings. Add tomatoes, sour cream, macaroni and seasonings.
Cover and cook slowly 10 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking until macaroni is tender.
Sometimes a little water needs to be added.
I usually use half the recipe.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Have beer at room temperature, but not flat.
Mix the ingredients like you would any biscuit recipe, roll, cut into round shapes.
Bake at 375°.

title: black forest parfait
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk on low speed until smooth. Add pudding and rest of milk until smooth.
Spoon half of pudding in dishes.
Sprinkle with wafer crumbs.
Cover with pie filling. Top with remaining pudding.
Garnish with cherries and crumbs. Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinated salad
directions: Wash and cut into small pieces.
Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over vegetables and cheese.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: pecan pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour into uncooked pie crusts. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 16 servings.

title: roast prime rib(or any good tender cut)
directions: Put in oven at 425 degrees for 40-45 minutes at around 11 or 12 noon. Then turn oven off; leave roast in oven and DON'T PEEK until ready to serve.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve with several different types of fruit.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and sugar; form into balls.
Put in fridge to chill.
Melt chocolate, paraffin and butter in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture; place on wax paper.

title: cabbage meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; make into 8 balls.
Wrap each ball in the bottom of baking pan.
Put in meat balls, then a small layer of cabbage on top.
Add just enough water to cover and bake in slow oven about 2 hours.

title: southern barbecue sandwich
directions: Place steak in large resealable plastic food bag.
Pour 1/2 cup Worcestershire sauce, mustard, red hot sauce and hickory salt over steak in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil over high heat. Reduce to low heat.
Cook for 5 minutes until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix together sugars, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
If adding coconut, etc., put in last.
Form into balls approximately 1 to 1 1/2-inches. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes approximately 10 dozen cookies.

title: kielbasa bean soup
directions: In large kettle combine celery, potatoes, carrots and onion with 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add soup and kielbasa.
Add extra water if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer.

title: old fashioned bean patties
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Spoon out into patties in hot fat.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.
Beans may be substituted with grated raw squash.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels, melted oleo and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: date roll
directions: Combine sugar and milk; cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Add the dates and allow to melt.
Cook slightly and beat until creamy. Add 2 cups chopped nuts.
Pour onto a damp tea towel and roll to form a 1 1/2-inch roll.
Roll in 1 cup of nuts, cut fine.
Allow to stand in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Cut into slices 1/2 inch thick.

title: meatballs for spaghetti
directions: In large bowl mix chopped chuck, bread wet with water and squeezed out, eggs bread crumbs, salt, pepper, parsley, cheese and garlic salt.
Mix just enough to blend.
Form into balls and fry in heavy skillet with oil.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Layer in order given.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 2 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Cool, debone and slice.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Saute onion and okra in melted margarine.
Cook chicken in water; remove and debone.
To broth, add tomato paste, crab boil, chicken and sauteed vegetables (celery, green pepper and garlic should be sauteed along with onion and okra, if desired.)
Add salts and roux.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and place in a greased pizza pan. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: beer-battered vidalia onion rings
directions: Peel, slice and separate onions into rings. Mix flour, chili powder, salt and pepper in large bowl, then whisk in beer until smooth. Heat a few inches of peanut oil in a deep pan for 5 to 10 minutes. Coat onion rings in batter, then drop carefully in oil and fry 3 to 5 minutes, until crispy. Drain on paper towel and salt to taste before serving.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald cornmeal with water; add milk, salt and beaten egg yolks; beat well.
Add baking powder and butter.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish that has been greased well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pre-tossed salad
directions: Place in layers in flat glass pan in order given.
Do not toss or mix.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: beef liver hash
directions: Brown and partially fry
liver in skillet with oil.
Cook potatoes, onions, salt and pepper until potatoes are almost done. Cut liver into small chunks and add to potato soup mixture. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add oats and peanut butter.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and
milk together.
Add to the butter that you have melted in
a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Completely cover with peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: leann's lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna as directed.
Brown beef and onions; add spaghetti sauce to beef mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Spread small amount of meat mixture on bottom of rectangular casserole dish. Make 3 layers in following order:
lasagna noodles, mixture, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Place in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: dried beef and chicken casserole
directions: Butter lightly flat casserole (13 x 9-inch) dish.
Layer beef slices in bottom of dish.
Wrap each chicken breast with bacon; place on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 275°, uncovered, for 3 hours or 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut and dice squash.
Cook in boiling water until tender; then drain.
In a casserole dish combine squash, sour cream, soup, 1 cup bread crumbs, egg, pimento, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix well.

title: pepper steak
directions: Melt
butter
in
skillet,
add beef and garlic.
Saute until browned.
Remove
meat
and
add onion and green pepper. Saute two minutes.
Return
meat
and add tomatoes to skillet with bouillon beef cube.
Simmer (15 to 20 minutes) for round. Blend
remaining ingredients and add to meat mixture, stirring constantly, for
a couple of minutes until thick.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: coffee punch
directions: Boil 1 gallon water; mix in the coffee, sugar and half and half.
Cool overnight.
Mix in ice cream.

title: quick and easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables and soup together.
Pour in pie shell and top with the the other pie shell - cut some slits in top.
Bake at 375 for at least 30 minutes checking to see if top is brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy cutout cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat margarine with electric mixer on medium speed until softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add milk and beat well.
Gradually beat in flour until well mixed.

title: chili corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Season to taste and serve.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Pour into a tube pan. Bake at 350° for
1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cheerios nuggets
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Grease 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans or 1 (10 x 15-inch) jelly roll pan.
Heat brown sugar, oleo, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart pan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly around edges.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda until foamy and light colored.
Pour over cereal, peanuts and raisins in greased 4-quart bowl.
Stir until mixture is coated.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Stir; let sit about 10 minutes. Loosen from pan; let sit another 30 minutes.
Break into bite size pieces.
Makes about 10 cups snack.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Cook 14 hours.
Keeps for months in fridge.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla, oil, pineapple and grated zucchini.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add nuts, cherries or raisins; mix together.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown. Grate zucchini skins, insides and seeds all together.
Spoon out excess seeds.

title: tasty muffin snack(makes 1 dozen)
directions: You will need 2 greased mini muffin pans.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips together.
Take off heat.
Add cereal; mix.
Shake in bag of powdered sugar.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells and drain on paper towels.
Brown meat with salt, pepper and a little garlic powder and basil if you like.
Mix all ingredients except sauce and Mozzarella.
Stuff the shells.
Put a little sauce in bottom of 11 x 14-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Put the shells in.
Cover with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with some Parmesan cheese and the Mozzarella.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt, drain and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine soup and cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and eggs.
Pour over broccoli.
Put bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Mix together broccoli, soup, rice, onion, celery, cheese whiz, and 1 cup cheddar cheese.
Season to taste.
Top casserole with remaining cup of shredded cheddar cheese.
Place in a 9 x 13 inch ovenproof dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge frosting\(microwave dish)
directions: Put chocolate, sugar, milk, butter and salt in a 4-cup glass measuring cup or microproof dish.
Cook on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir after 1 minute; add vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until almost cool.
Add nuts.
Beat or stir until spreading consistency reached.
Makes 1 cup.

title: black bottom ice cream pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips in cream, stirring occasionally.
Add vanilla.
Chill until thickened.
Spoon chocolate ice cream into crust.
Spread 3/4 of chocolate sauce over ice cream.
Return to freezer, then spoon vanilla ice cream over chocolate sauce. Drizzle remaining chocolate sauce over top of pie.
Freeze. Serves 6.

title: watergate cake
directions: Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and onion in a bowl.
Beat together vinegar, milk, salad dressing, salt and dry mustard.
Mix with cabbage. Cover and refrigerate several hours to let flavors blend. Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Serves 3.

title: northwest cheesecake supreme
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and flour, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla; pour over crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 250°.
Continue baking 1 hour.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.
Top with pie filling before serving.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, butter, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Mix together crushed pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes in oven preheated to 325°.
Allow to cool.
Then mix together the cream cheese, rest of sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour this mixture over top of pretzel mixture and refrigerate for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter soup with pepper jelly(a spicy peanut butter soup with peanuts)
directions: Melt butter
in a saucepan over low heat; add onion and celery.
Saute
for
about 5 minutes.
Add flour and mix until well blended.
Stir
in
chicken broth and allow to simmer for about
minutes.
Remove from heat; strain broth.
Stir the peanut
butter,
salt
and cream into the strained broth until well
mixed.
Serve hot.
Garnish each serving with a teaspoon of chopped peanuts and dollop of jelly.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix orange jello with hot water.
Mix gelatine mixture, cranberry sauce and celery with crushed pineapple.
Add walnuts and apples.
Mix together.
Put in 10 1/2 x 6 1/2-inch long glass dish. Chill until set.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix and other ingredients together in a large bowl and beat for about 2 minutes.
Bake in a large pan for about 1 hour.

title: squash doggers
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in hot oil like corn doggers.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix and pat first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over first layer.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine well.
Pour over broccoli and toss to coat.
Add bacon and toss.
Cover and put into refrigerator at least 3 hours before serving.

title: tomato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter and oil until soft.
Add chopped tomatoes, thyme, basil, parsley and black pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix flour with 1/2 cup of the chicken broth until smooth.
Add the 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth and chicken-flour mixture to the tomatoes.
Add baking soda, sugar, cream and pinch of salt to the tomatoes.
Simmer on low for 25 minutes.

title: caramel crunch
directions: Combine
butter,
sugar, brown sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in 2 quart saucepan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring until sugars
are dissolved.
Using a candy thermometer, cook syrup
to hard
ball	stage (250°).
Pour syrup over combined popcorn
and peanuts
in a large bowl or Dutch oven.
Stir to coat
evenly using
a
long
handled spoon as mixture is hot. Allow to cool and break into clusters.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Place butter in pan and melt on low heat.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in pan until tender.
Add cream cheese already softened, Ranch party mix, mayo and crabmeat.
Mix together and put in a casserole dish.
Cook for 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: chocolate maple nut bars(makes 24 to 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt; cut in margarine until crumbly. Stir in 1 beaten egg. Press evenly into 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 25 minutes. Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, remaining 1 egg and flavoring; stir in nuts. Sprinkle chips evenly over prepared crust. Top with nut mixture. Bake 25 minutes longer or until golden. Cool. Cut into bars. Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows together over low heat.
Pour melted ingredients over popcorn.
Add oil, peanuts, M&M's and candy corn.
Press into a buttered Bundt or tube pan.
Cool 30 to 45 minutes in refrigerator.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and mustard in saucepan.
Gradually blend in milk and vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils 1 minute.
Stir at least half of hot mixture slowly into egg yolks.
Stir this mixture into remaining hot mixture in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Cool.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Spread rice in a greased shallow 3-quart baking dish. Top with chicken and mushrooms. Pour orange juice and broth over all. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken juices run clear and rice is tender. Garnish with oranges, paprika and parsley, if desired. Yield: 4 servings.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Flake and drain salmon.
Combine salmon, 4 ounces of the whipped cream cheese, chili sauce, dill weed, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, onion powder, garlic powder, red hot pepper sauce and liquid smoke, blending well.
Turn into a 2-cup mold.
Cover; chill overnight.
Unmold onto serving platter.

title: green beans(spanish style)
directions: Cook beans in small amount of boiling salted water until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan and saute onions until golden.
Add chili sauce and seasonings; simmer to combine flavor.
Pour hot sauce over hot beans and sprinkle with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add beaten eggs and pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: baked custard
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add scalded milk gradually.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart pan.
Set in pan with 1-inch water.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until set. A silver knife inserted should come out clean.

title: easy spanish rice
directions: Combine all three ingredients in vented microwave-safe dish. Cook on full power for 8 minutes.
Let set two minutes; fluff with fork and serve.

title: mississippi mud cake(served at pool party)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat by hand.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt and mix with mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a sheath pan.
Take cake out of oven and spread Marshmallow Creme on while hot, then cool.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In blender, combine honey, salt, mustard, paprika, lemon and orange rinds and lemon and orange juices.
Blend together. Continue blending while adding salad oil.
Transfer into salad dressing bottle.
Add poppy and shake.

title: hot salmon salad
directions: Melt margarine and brown onion.
Add milk.
Warm, do not boil.
Add crackers (crumbled) and drained salmon.
Takes just a few minutes to cook down.
Watch closely and stir often so that it doesn't burn.
Add hard boiled eggs last.

title: mocha nut butter balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts.
Shape in 1 inch balls and put on cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the pretzels, 3 tablespoons of sugar and the melted butter or margarine.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: boeuf bourguignon(from the cordon bleu cooking school, paris)
directions: Cut beef into cubes and brown quickly in hot butter.
Remove from skillet into casserole.
Heat brandy in a little saucepan until you can light the fumes and pour over meat.
Brown onions and mushrooms in skillet and remove into casserole.
Pour the wines into skillet; add stock, meat glaze, tomato paste and thicken with cornstarch or potato flour.
Pour over the meat, mushrooms and onions (having seasoned with salt and pepper) and simmer until tender (about an hour at 300° should do it). Sprinkle with chopped chives.
Good served with noodles, dressed with buttered crumbs.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onion.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings. Combine dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Add egg, milk and 1 teaspoon oil.
Beat until smooth.
Dip onion ring into batter.
Fry in deep hot oil at 375° until done.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour and sift (for a softer rounded cookie, add 1/4 cup more flour).
Stir dry ingredients together.
Blend in mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease baking dish.
Slice apples.
Place in baking dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar and lemon juice.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican flour tortillas
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour with salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Slowly add water.
Knead dough and roll into balls the size of golf balls.
Roll out flat and thin.

title: summer orange drink
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth (about 30 seconds).
Serve immediately.
A delightfully refreshing summertime drink.

title: brown rice pilaf
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Add all ingredients except celery and bake, covered, 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Stir in celery and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: party mix
directions: Bring oleo, brown sugar and Karo to boil.
Let boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Take off heat.
Add vanilla and soda.
Stir real good.
Drizzle over cereal and nuts.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Pour out on waxed paper and break up while it cools.
Real good.

title: scottish rite bean soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, tomato juice and water.
Soak beans 8 hours or overnight.
Chop peppers, celery and onions.
Add these and broken up tomatoes to drained beans.
Add beef, ham and seasoning and simmer until beans are done.
Can be cooked in a crock-pot on high for 8 hours or longer.
Fills a 3 1/2-quart crock-pot.
Makes a thick soup.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into casserole. Sprinkle with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.
Grated cheese, instead of bread or cracker crumbs, is also good.

title: macaroni stroganoff
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, brown the ground beef.
When brown, drain all grease.
After draining the grease, stir in uncooked macaroni, 3 1/3 cups of hot water, garlic, onion, Cheddar cheese and buttermilk.
Heat to a boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat, stirring occasionally; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook until desired consistency.
Serves 5.

title: hot potato fry balls
directions: Saute onion and garlic in the butter until golden brown.
Add the beef, chili and nutmeg and toss over a heat until the meat browns well.
Stir in shallots and cook three more minutes. Combine with the potatoes and add the egg yolks.
Beat until well combined.
Cool and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Roll into balls the size of an egg.
Beat egg whites until just frothy.
Dip balls into egg whites.
Deep fry in 350° to 375° oil until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Yield:
6 to 8.

title: hot sauce
directions: Place in a food processor; puree for 5 seconds.
Or, place in a blender; puree for 10 seconds.

title: braised leeks
directions: Halve
leeks
lengthwise
to 1 inch from bottom.
Rinse under cold
water to remove all sand; set aside.	Cook carrot, onion, celery and garlic in 1 tablespoon of butter in a medium skillet over
medium heat until tender, about 8 minutes.
Add leeks; cook 2
minutes.
Stir
in
wine and broth.
Cover and simmer
until tender,
about
30	minutes.
Remove
leeks
to serving
plate. Increase
heat to medium-high.
Add remaining butter.
Boil
until butter melts and juices reduce slightly, about 2 minutes.	Pour over leeks.

title: "it" chicken
directions: Combine rice, onion soup mix, mushroom soup, water and mushroom buttons in bowl, mixing well.
Brown chicken breasts in oleo and pour combined ingredients in greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Put chicken breasts on top of rice mixture, breast side down. Pour remaining oleo over completed dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crunchy apple snack
directions: Spread a small amount of peanut butter on each apple slice. Then roll in the cornflake crumbs and enjoy!

title: homemade pimentos
directions: In August, locate large red sweet peppers at local vegetable stand or outlet, 6 for $2.00.
Sliver and put into heavy kettle. Add chili powder and lemon juice according to taste and water to cover, plus 1 inch.
Cover and slowly simmer for 24 hours.
Cool and put in pint jars.
Refrigerate if not tightly sealed.
You'll have enough to last the winter.

title: sweet and sour sauce for meatballs
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and bouillon in saucepan.
Add water, vinegar, pineapple juice, soy sauce and butter.
Cook and stir until mixture is boiling.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Chill until ready to mix with browned meatballs.

title: beef corn dandy
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper; drain.
Add seasonings. Add tomatoes and corn.
Cook until hot and bubbly.
Add cubed cheese; stir and serve.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion; stir in salt.
Put in baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour onto meat.
Bake 25 minutes, then top with sauce and cheese.
Bake 8 more minutes.

title: old south cucumber pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamelware for 12 hours or overnight.
Wash 3 times in clean water and soak in fresh ice water for 3 hours.

title: ruthie's cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Roll into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: white lightning chili
directions: Wash beans, cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain beans and return to pot.
Add 3 cans of broth, garlic, onion, spices and salt to beans.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining can of broth, chicken, chilies, water and jalapeno.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over All Bran and Crisco.
Then add sugar, beaten eggs, 100% Bran, buttermilk and remaining ingredients. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a heavy saucepan; stir well.
Combine egg yolks and milk; gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil approximately 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and vanilla. Immediately pour into pastry shell.
Cover filling with wax paper. Let cool 30 minutes, then chill until firm.

title: reuben sandwich(to serve at tree trimming party)
directions: Adjust oven rack to lowest position.
Heat oven to 400°.
Have a cookie sheet ready.
Spread one side of bread with oleo.
Place 4 slices butter side down on cookie sheet.
Cover each with one slice Swiss cheese, 1 tablespoon dressing, 1/4 of sauerkraut, 1/4 of corned beef, another tablespoon of dressing and another slice of cheese.
Cover with remaining bread, butter side up.
Bake about 20 minutes, turning sandwiches once.
Makes 4.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat jello and pineapple until jello is completely dissolved. Set aside until completely cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip. Mix all together.
Chill until firm and cold.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil onion and chicken until done. Save broth. Debone chicken and mix with soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Crush Doritos and add all ingredients together. Then mix 2 cups of chicken broth and mix well. Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: In a medium size bowl, mash avocados.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
This may be used as a topping or garnish for tacos or enchiladas.

title: blueberry pie
directions: *If frozen blueberries are used, substitute cornstarch for flour.

title: chili cheese cubes
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until light.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to eggs; mix well.
Fold in cheeses and chilies.
Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into small squares; serve hot.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen appetizers.

title: marinated salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a 9-inch square baking dish. Pour dressing over vegetables, tossing to coat.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Drain, reserving dressing.
Arrange vegetables over lettuce.
Serve with reserved dressing and freshly cracked pepper.

title: chili con carne with tomatoes
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes (with liquid) and remaining ingredient except kidney beans.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Stir in kidney beans; heat through.
Makes 4 or 5 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: coconut orange balls
directions: Mix crushed wafers, sugar and nuts.
Add undiluted orange juice.
Last add melted butter and mix well.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: dot's cinnamon rolls
directions: In a well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan, distribute chopped nuts evenly over the bottom of pan.
Place on top of that layer a single layer of Riches frozen dinner rolls.
Next, sprinkle 1/2 package of the dry pudding.
Melt stick of butter.
Add brown sugar, Karo and cinnamon.
Pour this over the top of the rolls, then sprinkle on the raisins.
Cover with a damp towel; let sit overnight.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Turn upside down to cool.
Serves 10.

title: cream spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill for several hours to blend the flavors.
Serve with crisp vegetables, crackers or a hollowed out sourdough round bread.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients well.
Add the remaining ingredients and form into a ball.
Chill until firm.
Remove and garnish with parsley and pimiento strips.
Serve with crispy crackers.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place chicken in 4 pieces of heavy-duty foil, a quarter on each slice.
Add vegetables, dividing equally.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour soup over each quarter, close foil and place in shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients.
Pour mixture over the sliced tomatoes.
Marinate 1 hour. Grill or broil.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan melt butter; saute onions and garlic until tender.
Add 1/4 cup olives, green chilies, sour cream and soup; mix well.
Reserve 1 cup sauce; set aside.
Add chicken and 1/2 cup of cheese to remaining sauce.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture; roll up and place in ungreased baking dish. In a small bowl combine reserved sauce and milk.
Spoon over tortillas.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and olives.
Serves 8.

title: spinach and dill dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley and dill weed.
Stir in spinach until well combined.
Cover and refrigerate three to four hours.
Stir and serve with crackers. Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; bring to a hard rolling boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Mix together cranberries, nuts and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread in bottom of 9-inch greased pan.
Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, margarine, eggs and flavoring.
Pour over cranberry mixture.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Make spaghetti mix by directions on box.
In skillet, brown meat, onion, peppers, salt and pepper.
Add Ragu sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour meat mixture and spaghetti together.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Place pineapple in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Heat reserved juice and water mixture to boiling; dissolve lime gelatin in hot juice.
Pour over pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Beat cream cheese with sugar until soft and smooth.
Gradually blend in milk and vanilla.
Soften unflavored gelatin in cold water, heat to dissolve.
Blend into cheese mixture and pour over lime layer.
Chill until firm. Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water; add strawberries. Cool to room temperature.
Pour over cheese layer.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: chop suey dish
directions: Cube raw chicken and pork.
Add to peanut oil which has been heated in a heavy skillet.
Stir over low heat until meat is white. Add 1/2 cup chicken broth, celery which has been cut in strips, soy sauce, sugar and salt to taste.
Cover and cook on low heat until celery is tender but still crisp.
Mix 1 teaspoon cornstarch with 1/2 cup water or broth.
Stir into the meat mixture, bring to a boil, then add water chestnuts and bamboo shoots which have been chopped.
Cover and simmer a few minutes.
Serve over Chinese crispy noodles or over hot steaming rice.
Add the almonds at serving time.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 7 g, protein 25 g, fat 23 g, calories 339.

title: smucker's toppings summertime trifle(prep time:  15 minutes)
directions: Whisk milk and pudding for 2 minutes in a bowl.
Stir in pineapple.
Place angel food cake pieces on bottom of a separate, large, clear glass bowl.
Spread 1/3 of pudding mixture on top. Cover with sliced strawberries.
Spread layer of whipped topping over strawberries.
Pour half the jar of Smucker's| Toppings over layer.
Spread another 1/3 of pudding mixture on top.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Cover bananas with remaining 1/3 pudding mixture. Spread whipped topping over all.
Drizzle with Smucker's| Toppings.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Keep Trifle chilled until serving.
Garnish with strawberries and bananas when served, if desired.

title: lemon pie
directions: Wash lemon; slice and cube.
Use rind, but remove seeds.
Place all ingredients in blender; process well, using high speed.

title: cheese ball
directions: If onion is too strong, cut back a little.
I use pecans with this recipe.
Mix all ingredients in bowl except 1 cup nuts. Chill before forming into ball.
Form into ball and roll in remaining nuts.
Garnish and serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook butter and sugar to a rolling boil.
Add other ingredients; stir well.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: chicken chalupa
directions: Cook and cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute onion and celery in a little butter.
Blend soups, broth, green chilies, onion and celery.
Pour half of soup mixture into large baking dish.
Put half of the chicken on top of the above mixture and all of the tortillas, torn up.
Layer remaining chicken and soup mixture. Bake at 350° until bubbly. Top with cheese and melt.

title: chicken with mushroom gravy
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and garlic.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes, until juices run clear.
Remove chicken from skillet; add mushrooms and onion. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Season with salt and pepper. Add sherry or water and bring to a boil.

title: low cholesterol chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips and cereal.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: chocolate nut brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Let cool.
Beat eggs; add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat until light.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Add flour.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cook in a 325° oven for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, egg, onion, salt, pepper and broccoli.
Pour in greased casserole; sprinkle cheese on top. Melt margarine; mix well with stuffing and sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda, spices and salt.
Stir into molasses mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Slightly flatten.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: seasoned salt potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Spread 1 Tbsp. olive oil in a 10 x 15 inch baking sheet.
Add potatoes grease on both sides.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and table salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until tender flipping potatoes over after 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix and cream flour, oleo and powdered sugar.
Pat out on greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: puppy chow(serves a lot!!)
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips in medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour Chex into a covered container large enough to "shake."
Pour chocolate mixture over Chex.
Stir gently until coated.
Pour 1/2 powdered sugar onto Chex.
Cover and shake until coated.
Pour remainder of powdered sugar and shake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crispy. Drain on paper towel. Crumble and set aside.

title: scramble egg cookie(no bake)
directions: Combine with melted butter in skillet all ingredients except Rice Krispies and coconut; boil 10 minutes, then cool.
Add 2 cups Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonful in coconut and roll in balls.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Take out 1 cup of mix and add the nuts to it for the topping.
Set topping mix aside.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter, dipped in baking mix.

title: rice custard
directions: Add rice to milk in double boiler.
Cook, covered, over boiling water, until tender, about 1 hour.
Beat egg yolks well.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar; salt.
Stir in some of the hot rice mixture. Return to double boiler; cook 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove; partially cool.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites quite stiff. Slowly add 3 tablespoons sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold into rice custard.
Chill.
Serve as is with cream or whipped cream.

title: ham and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.

Mix other ingredients, except milk. In large casserole, place layer of spaghetti, then top with layer of mixed ingredients. Continue layering until all ingredients are used, with last layer being mixture.
Place cheese slices and butter pats on top.
Cover with milk to about an inch from casserole dish top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, then uncover and bake another 5 minutes.
Serve with hot bread and salad.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream margarine; add egg, vanilla and sugars, mixing until creamy.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased sheet.
Press with back of lightly floured fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Cook until done.
Drain well. Add all ingredients together, stir well and simmer several hours over low heat.
Check it every little bit to make sure it isn't sticking and stir.
(I love to cook this on our wood stove!)

title: texas beef skillet
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, beans, uncooked rice, green pepper, chili powder, garlic and 1 1/2 cups water.
Add Tabasco sauce to spice it up.
Bring to boiling and simmer, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Shred 1 to 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese and top with it.
Serve over corn chips.

title: mike's tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine tuna and 3/4 cup of cheese. I use sharp Cheddar cheese and I dice it instead of grating.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add salt, egg, warm water or milk and yeast mixture.
Begin adding flour to make a stiff dough. Turn into a greased bowl and cover with cloth.
When double in bulk, knead and roll out.
Cut out and place on pans brushed with butter or margarine.
Brush tops of rolls with butter.
Let rise in a warm place.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peggy's mexican cheese dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
You can top with optional ingredients of chopped spring onions (the green part), sliced mushrooms and sliced black olives.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until cheese melts.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Then eat with tortilla chips.

title: wine coolers
directions: Fill pitcher half full with ice cubes.
Add all ingredients and stir.
A sprig of mint is nice if you have it.
Serves 6.

title: kolache topping
directions: Mix all together well.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill about 4 hours.

title: nan's sausage & wild rice
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, then saute onions and mushrooms in the sausage grease.
Drain well.
Cook rice as directed.
Mix the above ingredients well.
Make cream sauce of chicken broth, flour and butter.
Mix all together and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: candied apples
directions: In large skillet, put water, sugar and red hots.
Cook until red hots melt.
Put apples in syrup and cook until apples are tender.
Turn apples over while cooking.
Remove apples.
Put in a baking dish.
Cook syrup until it's waxy, then pour over the apples.
Refrigerate.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Grease one 15x10x1 inch pan (13x9x2 and 9x9x2 will work) with melted butter or margarine.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to flour mixture stir with fork until moist.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick on floured surface. Cut with 2 inch cutter.
Place close together in prepared pans.
Cover with damp cloth and allow to rise one hour.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Brush tops with melted butter or margarine.
Serve while hot.
Makes 30 to 40 biscuits.

title: christmas tree cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and egg.
Beat until light.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Chill for several hours or until firm enough to roll.
Roll 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cookie cutter.
Bake on cookie sheets in moderate oven at 325° for about 8 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar in large bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in bananas, milk and vanilla; blend.
Stir in flour.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mini chocolate mint sandwiches
directions: To make filling combine milk and pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk, rotary beater or electric mixer at lowest speed for 1 to 2 minutes. Refrigerate 5 to 7 minutes or until partially set. Fold in whipped topping.

title: tostada pizza
directions: Mash avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper; mix.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Layer bean dip, avocado mixture and sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle over top: onions, tomatoes, olives and grated Cheddar cheese.
Use round pizza pan.
Serve with Tostito chips.

title: hot apple-cinnamon punch
directions: Put ingredients in large cooking pot.
Heat to boiling point. Stir from time to time so red hots won't stick to bottom of pan. Pour in cups and serve.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add bananas, then 2 cups flour. Reserve 2 tablespoons of flour to coat blueberries.
Place remaining dry ingredients, sift and fold into the banana mixture. Stir in vanilla.
Sprinkle flour over berries, then fold into batter.
Divide batter into loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cocido
directions: In 5-quart saucepan lightly brown chorizo.
Remove with slotted spoon.
To drippings in pan add stew meat.
Just before it is finished browning, add onions; stir to brown lightly.
Add chorizo, carrots, tomatoes and beef bouillon.
Simmer covered until beef is tender and carrots done.
Skim off some of the fat.
Add peas and steamed yams plus their juices, salt and pepper.
Reheat.

title: orange rice
directions: In wide saucepan, heat oil.
Add orange zest and rice; saute 2 minutes or until rice turns milky white.
Add the salt and water; heat to boiling.
Stir to mix; cover.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan. Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add mashed bananas.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt; mix in gradually.
Gradually add buttermilk and mix well.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat 1 cup pear juice to boiling.
Add gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir mayonnaise into cream cheese with fork, blending until smooth.
Add Cool Whip. Slowly stir into Jell-O mixture.
Crush pears to pulp with fork and add to Jell-O.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Bring broth to boil.
Add rice and seasoning packet.
Cook according to directions on package until rice is tender and broth is absorbed.
Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Put into a greased 2-quart casserole or 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Cover lightly with foil during first part of baking time; remove foil so mixture browns slightly.

title: cheese-scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in 1-inch of boiling salted water until tender.
Drain.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Strawberries to be preserved should first be washed thoroughly in cool water.
Do not stem berries until after washing.
After washing and stemming berries, place in a shallow container and sprinkle with sugar.
(This is extra sugar and is not measured from the five pounds to be used later.)
Let berries stand in sugar for three hours; of if desired, place in refrigerator overnight.

title: reese's cups(makes 100 to 400 pieces)
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar and vanilla until consistency to form into balls.
Roll into marble size balls.
Melt wax and chocolate in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate using toothpick.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: mom's chocolate surprise
directions: Flatten each biscuit and place one Kiss or 1/2 Kiss and 1/2 caramel in center of biscuit.
Pinch biscuit closed.
Roll in melted butter then cinnamon and sugar.
Layer biscuits in a Bundt pan that has been greased with Crisco.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Layer bean dip and put a layer of avocado dip on a large plate or platter.
Combine mayo, sour cream and taco mix.
Mix well. Spread on top.
Next, add scallions, tomatoes, olives and cheese. Serve with corn chips.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir by hand to mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sophia's tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients adding enough flour to roll. Cut into cookies. Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken in red wine(low-fat version)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in an ovenproof casserole.
Top with onions and mushrooms.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Remove and discard bay leaf before serving.
Each serving:
261 calories, 10 grams fat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coca-cola chocolate cake
directions: Sift the sugar and flour together.
Combine the margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add the chocolate mixture to the sugar-flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Fold in marshmallows.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cook noodles as directed.
Serve stroganoff over noodles.

title: green bean salad
directions: Cook beans just until tender and drain.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble.
Mix beans, bacon and onion rings.
Combine remaining ingredients in dressing except cheese.
Add cheese at last minute. Make 3 to 4 hours ahead of time.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water. Put 1/4 cup boiling water in mixer bowl. Add dissolved gelatine. Stir to thoroughly mix. When mixture cools, add pudding mix, spice and milk. Beat at low speed until mixture is smooth, about 2 minutes. Add pumpkin and brown sugar substitute. Beat until well blended. Pour into 2 cooked pie shells. Can pour in bowl and serve as a pudding. Makes 2 pies.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour ginger ale in right before serving.
Serves 35 to 40 people.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Mix

Stir soda into buttermilk. Add

Dip out with
