with a mustard relish.
Yields approximately 60.

title: chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir while baking and add more broth when needed.

title: maple glazed sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish, alternate potatoes and apples in rows, packing tightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan, bring to a boil and pour hot, over apples and potatoes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients and put some on the bottom of brisket and the rest over the top.
Seal tightly in foil and bake in slow oven at 325° for 3 hours or until tender.

title: roast potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut each potato into quarters.
Place potatoes in large roasting pan with olive oil and remaining ingredients.
Shake and toss to coat.
Roast for 20 minutes or until tender and golden brown, stirring halfway through cooking.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Combine coconut and margarine; press into an 8-inch pie pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool thoroughly.

title: bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt oleo on cookie sheet in oven to remove pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add milk to stir until it makes a dough.
Put on floured surface to roll around to cover dough.
Knead about 10 times and roll out. With floured knife, cut dough in half, then cut in 1/2-inch strips. Dip each strip in melted butter on both sides.
Put in same pan. Shake garlic on it if you like.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Good dipped in hot pizza sauce.

title: candy basket
directions: Generous estimates to allow for errors and nibbling!

title: chili soup
directions: Cold pack 1 hour.

title: cantonese dinner
directions: Place all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high 3 hours.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Put crumbled crackers in bottom of baking dish, then put a layer of oysters and pepper.
Repeat layers, but make sure crackers are on top.
Pour milk over dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf(very old recipe)
directions: Mix all together.
Cook for 45 minutes in buttered pan. Put tomatoes on top 20 minutes before serving.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl, stirring well.
Add apples, milk, eggs and 1 tablespoon of oil. Stir mixture just until moist.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together, except for cheese.
Place half of mixture in greased pan, then cheese, then rest of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chewy marshmallow brownies
directions: Combine butterscotch chips and butter in a small saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until chips melt. Set aside.

title: stuffed sole with dill sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/3 cup butter.
Add celery and onion.
Saute.
Stir in stuffing, parsley, lemon juice, lemon peel and salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: stuffed mushrooms italian style
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Then rinse mushrooms and pat dry. Remove stems and reserve for later use.
Brush outsides of the caps with 4 tablespoons of the oil.
Sprinkle lightly with salt. Place cavity side up in a shallow baking pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients together. Boil, then cool.
Add sugar, salad oil and vinegar.
Mix all together and let stand overnight in the refrigerator in a covered dish.
Serves 12.
Very good with barbecue.

title: hummus bi tahini
directions: Place garlic in food processor; mince finely.
Add drained chickpeas and process 1 minute; scrape sides of processor.
Add paprika, 2 tablespoons olive oil, lemon juice and tahini. Continue processing.
Add reserved juice through feed tube while processing until mixture is the consistency of pancake batter. Add salt and pepper.
Pour onto serving plate.
Drizzle with remaining olive oil.
Top with parsley and a sprinkle of paprika. Serve as an appetizer with pita bread.
Makes about 2 to 3 cups.

title: black walnut apple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add sifted flour, soda and spices. Fold in chopped apples, walnuts and vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: orange-chocolate mousse
directions: In custard cup, sprinkle gelatin over cold water, let stand 1 minute. In small saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, and water. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until hot and slightly thickened. Remove from heat, add softened gelatin, stirring until dissolved. Blend in milk and vanilla; cool. In small mixing bowl, combine whipping cream and orange peel, beat until stiff. Gradually add chocolate mixture to whipped cream. Spoon into dessert dishes; refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned pot roast
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven on top of stove.
Sprinkle roast with dry mustard and garlic salt.
Brown both sides of roast adding mustard and garlic salt to both sides.
When nicely browned, add the can of French onion soup and 3/4 can of water. Simmer on medium heat for 2 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes to meat and continue to cook on medium heat 1 hour longer or until meat and vegetables are fork-tender.

title: szechwan chicken with spicy peanut sauce
directions: Place chicken in a 2-quart pan with onion, ginger, sherry, salt, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil over high heat, then cover.
Reduce heat and simmer until meat is done (about 20 minutes).
Meanwhile, prepare Peanut Sauce and place lettuce on individual plates.
When Peanut Sauce is ready, place chicken on lettuce and drizzle on Peanut Sauce.

title: easy cream cheese dessert
directions: Unroll package of crescent rolls and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spoon on top of crescent rolls.
Unroll second package of crescent rolls and pat on top.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Use a 2-quart casserole dish; put about half of the mixture in dish and top with crumb mixture.
Use balance of mixture, then balance of crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Finely chop or grate carrots.
Mix all ingredients well. Makes 6 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: rye dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except rye bread 24 hours ahead of serving. Tear center of round loaf into small dipping pieces; place pieces around outside of loaf on tray.
Use cavity of loaf as bowl for dip.
Prepare bread just before serving.

title: swiss cheese french bread
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add poppy seed and salt.
Cut French bread in 2-inch slices, taking care not to cut all the way through.
In each cut, place a slice of Swiss cheese.
Spoon onion mixture into each cut.
Wrap securely in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: turkey-noodle bake
directions: Blend milk into cream of mushroom soup; stir in beaten eggs. Add noodles, bread crumbs, cheese, green pepper, green onion, pimentos, margarine and turkey.
Turn into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Cut in squares to serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: one-step lasagne
directions: Combine water with spaghetti sauce in bowl.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 4-inch baking dish with 1 1/2 cups of sauce.
Arrange layer of uncooked noodles slightly overlapping, on top of sauce. Spread 1/2 the Ricotta and 1/2 the Mozzarella over noodles. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Add another 1 1/2 cups of sauce, repeat with another layer of noodles, the remaining cheeses and 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Top with layer of noodles and pour remaining sauce over noodles, spreading to cover.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Cover tightly with heavy foil, set on jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let set for 10 minutes before removing foil.

title: orange tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let egg whites warm to room temperature, about
1 hour.
Fill cup of flour lightly with salt. Beat egg yolks in small bowl for 3 minutes.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Continue beating until mixture is smooth.
At low speed, blend in flour mixture (in fourths) alternately with orange juice (in thirds).
Begin and end with flour mixture.
Add orange peel. In large bowl, beat egg whites at medium speed until foamy. Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar, beating after each addition. Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in the yolk mixture using under and over motion in egg whites.
Pour in a 10-inch tube pan (ungreased); bake 35 to 40 minutes, until cake springs back when gently pressed with fingertip.
Invert pan; cool completely about 1 hour.
Loosen from pan, using up and down motion.
Run spatula around edge of cake and tube.
Use serrated knife going back and forth.

title: mexican corn
directions: Pour 1 can whole kernel corn into a pot.
Turn stove to medium heat.
Pour bell pepper into the corn (red and green pepper).
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar, dash of salt and pepper each.
Stir ingredients into the corn.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes until hot.

title: egg noodles alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Add cheese, half and half and butter.
Mix and serve.

title: poke cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare, bake and cool cake mix as directed on package for two 9-inch round cake layers.
Place cake layers, top sides up, in 2 clean 9-inch round cake pans.
Pierce cake with a large fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Stir 1 cup boiling water into each flavor of gelatin in separate bowls 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Carefully pour red gelatin over 1 cake layer and lime gelatin over second layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours. Dip 1 cake pan in warm water 10 seconds; unmold onto serving plate.
Spread with about 1/4 of the frosting.

Unmold second cake layer and carefully place on first layer. Frost top and sides of cake with remaining frosting. Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve. Decorate as desired. Store leftover cake in refrigerator.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Cream the first three ingredients together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and salt.
Mix until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Divide batter in half and add chocolate to one-half.
Drop batter alternately by heaping teaspoonfuls into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Press down with spoon to smooth top, then run knife through batter several times to marbleize.
Bake in a moderate oven about 45 minutes.
When cooled, spread with frosting.
Makes approximately 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients into first mixture.
Add apples, vanilla and nuts.
Stir together.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Melt cheese in microwave.
Fry (scramble) and drain sausage. Mix sausage with cheese.
Add ketchup, garlic and oregano.
Spread cheese mixture onto slices of rye bread.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° on a cookie sheet.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: *I use Cool Whip (about 2 1/2 cups).

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Blend in flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and flavor.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in tube pan, well-greased and floured at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Combine avocados, lemon juice and pepper.
Combine seasoning mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Layer in a glass 9 x 13-inch pan the bean dip, guacamole, sour cream mix, tomatoes, scallions, black olives and cheese on top.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: beef and cheese turnovers
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and salt.
Cut in lard with a pastry blender until it forms coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle with ice water 1 tablespoon at a time, stirring until dough clings together.
Form into a smooth ball.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: white-ting-a-lings (microwave recipe)(sweet and salty flavors taste great in this fast and fun candy.)
directions: Line cookie sheets with waxed paper.
Place candy coating in medium microwave-safe bowl or 4-cup microwave-safe measuring cup. Microwave on Medium for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once halfway through melting.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheets.
Let stand until set.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, Veg-All, soup and sour cream.
Blend together.
Pour into pie shell (unbaked).
Cover with top crust. Brush top with egg and bake in preheated 350° oven until golden brown.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and margarine together and cook until mixture comes to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil this mixture for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in coconut and marshmallow cream.
Stir together until mixture is creamy and smooth.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan. Allow to cool and cut as desired.

title: pina colada salad
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin in medium bowl.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in pina colada concentrate and reserved pineapple juice until concentrate is melted.
Refrigerate about 45 minutes or until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites. Stir in pineapple and coconut.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Cover and refrigerate about 4 hours or until set; unmold.
Serves 8.

title: jalapeno quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl except butter.
Place half melted butter in bowl, other swish in Pyrex dish, 13 x 9-inch, swish around.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
This makes its own crust. (You can add more chilies for hotter flavor or diced jalapenos.)

title: crab louis in avocado halves
directions: Combine egg yolk, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar and beat with wire whisk.
Add oil gradually, beating rapidly. When thickened and smooth, add chili sauce, scallions and olives. Mix well and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Put crabmeat in mixing bowl and add one-half of the sauce.
Mix gently so as not to break up crab lumps.

title: popped rice casserole
directions: Put oil in a frying pan.
Add rice and saute until all rice has popped (changed color and nicely browned).
Stir constantly. Brown meat in another frying pan while rice is sauteing.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a large casserole.
Top with onion rings.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini crab cakes
directions: Squeeze grated zucchini as dry as possible.
Add ingredients and mix well.
Make into patties and dust with flour.
Pan-fry in oil until brown on both sides.

title: rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar. Let stand overnight (to make own juice).
If not enough juice, add 1/4 cup water.
Cook rhubarb and sugar until rhubarb is tender.
Add jello and put into jars. Freeze.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake slow until golden brown at 325°, about 45 minutes.

title: barbecue dove
directions: Soak doves in vinegar and sugar mixture.
Boil doves for 35 or 40 minutes.
Wrap each dove in bacon and secure with toothpick. Coat dove in barbecue sauce.
Cook on grill until bacon is done.

title: spring fever dip
directions: Heat soup and then add all other ingredients.
Serve warm.

title: butter sugar cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the first 3 ingredients.
Stir in milk and flavoring.
Combine sifted dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Chill dough.
Roll very thin.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly brown at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: three-cheese lasagna rolls
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain well and set aside.
Drain spinach; press between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Set spinach aside.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion, mushrooms, garlic and vermouth; saute until tender.
Transfer to a bowl; add spinach, Parmesan cheese and next 5 ingredients.

title: zucchini beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Slice zucchini in 2-quart dish. Mix onions, cracker crumbs and ground beef; salt and pepper. Spread on top of zucchini. Pour soup over mixture. Top with cheese. Bake in preheated oven 45 minutes. Makes about 4 servings.

title: chicken wings piri-piri
directions: Separate wings at joints.
Wash and pat dry.
Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate chicken in the mixture for 2 to 4 hours in the refrigerator, stirring occasionally to coat chicken. Chicken may then be broiled or grilled.

title: bavarian pot roast
directions: Brown roast in big pot.
Combine everything else in a separate pan and pour over meat.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender (all afternoon).
Take meat out. Thicken juices with cornstarch.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas; add all ingredients together.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt cheese and butter in a double boiler.
Combine with sifted flour and red pepper.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into small balls with palm of hands.
Pat thin or press with a fork on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Allow to completely cool, then store in an airtight container.

title: fried rice
directions: In 2 cups water, boil celery (and any other veggies) until tender.
Set aside liquid.
Melt butter in frypan.
Add sugar. Brown rice; don't burn.
Add celery and any other veggies.
Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add meat/fish.
Add soy sauce until liquid is absorbed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cornish hens with wild rice stuffing
directions: Saute celery, shallots and green peppers in 2 tablespoons oleo in a saucepan, Stir in next 3 ingredients; bring to a boil and add wild rice.
Cover and reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook about 25 minutes.
Remove giblets from hens and reserve for another use. Rinse with cold water and pat dry.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper inside and out.
Stuff lightly with rice mixture.
Secure cavities. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop skillet dinner
directions: Season pork chops with 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Brown chops in hot oil in large skillet.
Add tomato juice and water.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cabbage, carrots, onions, potatoes and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cover; simmer for 35 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: edible cookie bowl
directions: Batter: Cover outside of a loaf pan with foil, spray with vegetable spray.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients except 1/4 cup of cheese.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon in pan.
Top with cheese and crumbled potato chips.
Bake 60 to 90 minutes at 350°.

title: lo-fat slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
It is better if you let it marinate for a while.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
You can use any of your favorite vegetables.

title: pecan pie mini muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine first 3 ingredients. Set aside. Combine butter and eggs. Mix well. Stir into flour mixture until just moistened. Fill paper-lined miniature muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tested done. Remove immediately to cool on wire racks. Makes 3 dozen mini-muffins.

title: holiday salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Put lime jello and food coloring in bowl; add and beat in marshmallow mixture.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Stir in pineapple and juice. Add Cool Whip to gelatin mixture; add nuts and mayonnaise.
Pour into 9 x 15 pan.
Refrigerate and when completely set, pour over the red gelatin which has been made according to package directions.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: egg nog
directions: Stir together eggs, milk and sugar in a large saucepan (heavy pan).
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat and place in a bowl of ice water, stirring
1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and chill in refrigerator from 4 to 24 hours (depending when you need it).
At serving time, transfer chilled mixture to a punch bowl.
Fold in whipped cream and sprinkle nutmeg over entire top.
This is a great holiday drink that can be prepared well ahead of time.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° with water bath.
Place crumbs and softened butter in small bowl, mix and press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Be sure to line bottom of spring pan with wax paper and grease interior with butter.
In large mixing bowl, cream the cheese with sugar; add vanilla, sour cream, flour and lightly beaten eggs (in three parts), mixing only until blended after each addition.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool about 1 hour, free from drafts.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight before removing from pan and cutting.

title: country ham bake
directions: Put country ham in clean lard can or very large pot filled with hot water (just below the boiling point).
Let boil for 10 or 15 minutes.
This step gives the ham a good cleaning and removes excess salt from outside.
Remove ham and discard water.
Place ham in can and fill can half full with hot water.
Add 4 quarts ginger ale or cola drink and put top loosely on can.
Bring to a full rolling boil for 30 minutes.
The ginger ale or cola helps to bring out the flavor of the ham.
Place about 4 thicknesses of newspaper on the floor and set ham (still in can) on papers. Press lid on lightly; pull papers around sides and top of can and tie with string.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake according to instructions, adding 1/4 package coconut and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bundt cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until well blended.
Add egg substitute, a small amount at a time, and beat very well after each addition.
(This is very important with egg substitute.)
Add flour, vanilla, grated orange rind and lastly, nuts, that have been mixed with flour.
Bake about 1 hour in well-greased Bundt pan at 325° to 350°.
Serve plain or with lemon drizzle.

title: monterey bake
directions: Saute meat with garlic and onion powders in a lightly greased skillet about 10 minutes or until done.
Blend salt, liquid pepper, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Add this mixture and remaining ingredients, except corn chips, to ground beef.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with corn chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage, apple and pineapple salad
directions: Chop the cabbage medium;
sprinkle the lemon juice over the diced
apples
to
prevent
discoloration.
Combine
the pineapple,
cabbage,
salt,
the
cabbage and the apples.
Mix well
and add the salad dressing gradually, stirring until the salad is thoroughly mixed.
Serve on a lettuce leaf, or with a meal or as an appetizer.
Makes 3 to 5 pounds.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until transparent.
Mix all ingredients together and add enough broth to make soft mixture. Bake at 400° about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: lentil loaf
directions: Mash lentils a bit.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in a flat pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with tomato sauce.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great with ham.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand until mixed well.
Form into a loaf and place in a 9 x 13-inch oblong dish.
Pour more catsup on top of loaf and bake at 350°, covered, for 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook an additional 60 minutes.

title: apple pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Mix up all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve cold.
Feeds about 8 people.

title: summer squash casserole(low calorie)
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: yogurt dill bread
directions: Grease an 8-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, stir together 1 cup flour, yeast and dill weed; set aside.
In medium saucepan, heat and stir the yogurt, sugar, water, butter and salt just until warm (120° to 130°) and butter almost melts.
Add to flour mixture. Add egg.
Beat with electric mixer on low to medium for 30 seconds, scraping sides of bowl. Beat on high for 3 minutes. Stir in remaining flour.
Spoon batter into pan. Cover and let rise, about 30 minutes. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: crunchy delite
directions: In a double boiler, heat white chocolate slowly.
Do not allow hot water to touch chocolate.
Mix remaining ingredients with melted chocolate.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Allow to cool and harden.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then add the wet ingredients and mix. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken baste
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Boil about 5 minutes.
Baste chicken every 15 minutes.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
When cool, add whole cranberry sauce (juice and all).
Add can of crushed pineapple (drained).
Add ruby red wine.
Put in fridge until slightly set, then add chopped nuts.
Let mold.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together; place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: italian beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; simmer until onion is tender.

title: lemon basil grilled chicken
directions: Combine Puritan oil and next 7 ingredients in shallow baking dish.
Add chicken, turning once to coat both sides. Refrigerate for 30 to 45 minutes, turning once.
Prepare charcoal for grilling, or heat broiler.
Grill or broil chicken 4 inches from heat, turning once, 3 to 5 minutes per side or until completely cooked through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix all cake ingredients together.
Pour over nuts.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool. Invert on serving plate.
Prick top.
Drizzle and smooth glaze over top of cake.
Allow cake to absorb all of glaze.

title: grape leaf pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil.
Place 2 grape leaves in bottom of jar.
Place cucumbers and 8 grapes in jar.
Place 2 grape leaves on top of cucumbers.
Pour hot vinegar solution over cucumbers.

title: baked beans
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Cook until tender, then drain.
Add other ingredients and put into buttered casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy hash brown potatoes(serves 6 to 8 people)
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
In saucepan, combine soup, milk and cream cheese.
Stir and cook until smooth.
Put potatoes and onions in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over all and mix well.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake for 1 1/4 hours.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Wash berries and cut in half.
If not sweet, add a little sugar and set aside.
Slice pound cake and place all around bottom and sides of large bowl.
Mix pudding according to directions and mix with about 1/3 to 1/2 of whipping cream.
Put 1/2 of pudding mixture on top of cake.
Add berries.
Put rest of pudding mixture on top.
Finish by adding the last of whipped cream.
Place a few whole berries on top for garnish.

title: don's saturday night muffins
directions: Combine all-bran and milk.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Then add egg, oil and honey.
Mix together dry ingredients, then add to all-bran mixture.
Bake at 400° for 17 minutes and 30 seconds. Makes 12 muffins.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all together and cook.

title: sponge drops
directions: Sift flour, tartar, baking powder and baking soda well.
Using electric mixer, beat eggs at top speed for 5 minutes.
Add sugar a little at a time, then a capful of vanilla extract.
Now add flour mixture a little at a time.
Spray pans with vegetable shortening.
Spoon mixture onto cookie sheets by 1/2 teaspoon drops.
Bake at 350° until edges are light brown.
Remove from pan immediately onto paper dusted with powdered sugar.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.
Sort by size and make sandwiches with Cool Whip filling.

title: tex-mex layered dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper in bowl. Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix in bowl; blend well.
Spread bean dip on large platter.
Layer avocado mixture and sour cream mixture over bean dip.
Top with layers of onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: scrambled eggs deluxe
directions: Combine eggs and milk in a bowl and mix with a fork or whipping tool. Scramble eggs in a greased pan. Cook ring bologna in a pan or microwave. Once bologna is cooked, cut into small pieces and add to scrambled eggs. Let simmer together for about 5 minutes.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Beat together buttermilk, eggs and baking soda.
Beat in corn meal, sugar, salt and fat.
Stir in cracklins.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: new mexico green chile jam
directions: Combine ingredients and boil 30 minutes.
Cool and store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, syrup and boiling water in saucepan and cook until it spins a slight thread.
Fold in 2 cups of peanuts and cook until peanuts are done.
This takes about 15 or 20 minutes.
The only way you can tell if peanuts are done is by tasting them.
Stir to keep from sticking.
When peanuts are done, take up and add soda, mixing well.
Pour onto buttered baking sheet, not aluminum. Cool and break up into small pieces.

title: swiss delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Spread mixture onto cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk and pour onto cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip onto pudding mixture.
Freezes well.

title: dime a dozen
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and spoon small spoon-size drops onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix until smooth.
Pour into an 8-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake 25 minutes at 375° or until firm. Extra good.

title: bow knots
directions: You will need 24 toothpicks.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add to chicken broth which the spaghetti has been cooked in.
Add soups, mushrooms and pimento.
Cook slowly.
Add cheese and chopped chicken.
Continue to cook slowly.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in heavy saucepan.
Saute onion until soft, but not browned.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute, being careful not to burn.
Stir in rice.
Coat with butter mixture. Add broths, salt (if used) and pepper.
Cover.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chicken or pork adobo
directions: Cut pork or chicken into serving pieces.
Combine meat with all the ingredients and simmer until meat is done and sauce is thick.
Serve warm and with pickles for accompaniment.

title: rolled oats pie
directions: Mix all together, adding eggs last for 1 pie.
Bake in crust at 400°.

title: chicken in cantaloupe shells
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken, celery, almonds and orange sections.
In small bowl, blend together sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, ginger, orange peel, salt and nutmeg.
Add just enough dressing to chicken to coat well.
Chill.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg in a bowl.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves in another bowl.
Mix molasses and boiling water in a 2-cup measuring cup.
Add flour mixture and molasses mixture alternately to cream mixture, beating thoroughly for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Can be baked in a 9 x 12 inch pan for 40 minutes.

title: mexican dip #1
directions: In an 8 to 10-inch pie plate mix the beans with taco mix. Next layer is thawed guacamole, then tomatoes, then onions and then chilies.
Top with sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: taco cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wash day fruit cobbler
directions: In hot oven, melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients, add milk, stir and pour over melted oleo in baking dish.
Heat the fruit, spoon over batter.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven, or until top is nice and brown.

title: dorothy's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Mix all of the above together and alternate with vanilla wafers and bananas, ending with some pudding left to top the dessert.
Needs to be kept refrigerated.

title: orange salad with pecan dressing
directions: Pare and section oranges.
Cut each section into fourths.
Mix oranges and lettuce.
Mix the remaining dressing ingredients. Pour over the oranges and lettuce; toss.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package instructions.
Drain quickly, adding cream cheese and 1/2 stick of butter.
Stir until melted.
Season with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with stuffing, drizzle remaining melted butter over all.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: italian chicken and artichokes
directions: Saute for 5 minutes the following:
chicken breasts, garlic and butter.
Blend together chicken soup, Swiss cheese, white wine, Parmesan cheese and artichokes in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, garlic, oregano, fennel, salt and pepper.
Add pizza sauce and tomato sauce; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: honey chicken
directions: Baste chicken with butter or margarine first.
With skin side down, bake 40 minutes on broiler pan at 350°.
Put on half of the sauce.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Turn and put on remaining sauce and bake another 25 minutes.
Put lemon juice on top.

title: jean's baked beans
directions: Use 2 1/2-quart or larger baking dish.
Open cans and empty into baking dish.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved; add catsup and Worcestershire and stir in.
Add enough water to make "soupy"; put bacon strips on top and bake approximately 1 1/2 hours at 400°.
Will not be set completely when you shake dish.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat and	garlic	in
skillet;
drain fat.
Blend next 4 ingredients in bowl; stir in meat.	Fill each manicotti with 1/4 cup filling.
Place manicotti in single layer in 10 x 6 x
1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan,	after covering
with
any
remaining filling and sauce. Cover with foil.
Bake
in 325° oven 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken curry(serves 6 to 8 people)
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon and curry in saucepan.
Heat. Add to chicken and broccoli.
Top with muffin mix, cheese and butter.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 325°.
Great at a buffet!

title: taco salad(for a crowd)
directions: Combine lettuce, tomato and onion in a large bowl.
Prepare ground beef and taco mix as directed on package and cool slightly. Mix taco mixture, cheese and beans with lettuce.
Add salad dressing and toss gently.
Just before serving, crush up the chips and toss with the salad.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add parsley, lemon juice, mustard, horseradish, salt and milk.
When smooth, add shrimp and eggs.
Put in either scallop shells or small oven container.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes (or 375° for 20 minutes).

title: stairwell stew
directions: Trim and wipe stew meat thoroughly.
Combine all ingredients, except flour, water and Mozzarella cheese, in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for 10 to 12 hours (on high setting for 3 to 4 hours).

title: eggplant tomato casserole
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon. Set aside.

Saute green pepper and onion in drippings until tender. Add eggplant and tomatoes. Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in salt and pepper. Spoon eggplant mixture into a slightly greased 2-quart casserole dish and top with bacon. Sprinkle cheese over casserole. Top with bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple paradise pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Soften butter in mixing bowl.
Add the sugar, flour and coconut; mix well.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 or 12 minutes, or until brown. Crumble.
Press 2 cups into 9-inch pie pan.
Cool.
Reserve remaining mixture.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine 2 cups baking mix, white sugar, milk and egg. Pour into 9-inch round pan. Combine 1/3 cup baking mix, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon with a fork. Sprinkle over cake and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: easy raspberry ring
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
in
boiling
water.
Add frozen raspberries and stir until thawed. Chill until partially set. Whip Jell-O and raspberry mixture until fluffy and fold in whipped cream.

title: fried shrimp batter
directions: Peel peaches, puree in blender, add sugar to sweeten.
Add crushed ice.
Serve and Enjoy!

title: no sugar cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Mix dry ingredients; add raisins to dry mixture to coat.
Combine dry and wet mixture.
Mix well.
Don't beat.
Mix by hand.
Bake in well-greased loaf pans.
Fill very full, as cake rises very little.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: chili-cheesy rice
directions: Microwave onion on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Spoon half of rice mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole; top with half of cheese.
Repeat with remaining rice mixture and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done and cut up into chunks. Combine chicken, diced celery, diced onion, soup and milk into casserole dish.
Cook and drain noodles and add to other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits.
Add all ingredients together.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease 9-inch pie or cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until slightly brown or firm.
Cut in desired pieces and serve hot or cold.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven immediately, so it won't dry out.
Serves 12.

title: pecan tarties
directions: Mix together and press in small muffin tins.
Then fill with filling.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for an
hour in covered casserole.

title: apple butter
directions: Boil apples, sugar and vinegar for 20 minutes.
Add red hots.

title: mini beef loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, milk and bread crumbs.
Press 1/2 of the hamburger in bottom and 1/2 way up the sides of 12 ungreased muffin cups, then fill each with onion, pepper and cheese.
Top with the remaining hamburger and press edges to seal.
Place muffin pans on a jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water until thick.
Add cheese, butter and garlic salt.
Stir until melted.
Beat eggs lightly and stir into mix.
Put into buttered casserole and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, add sugar, margarine and cream.
Begin cooking on medium heat, stirring constantly after it starts cooking.
Reduce to low heat.
When you can drop a drop into a glass of cold water and it forms a soft ball, remove from heat. Beat in vanilla, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix well. Pour into a buttered pan while warm.
Serve.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Add cake mix to creamed oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, then vanilla.
Mix and beat.
Stir in sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Add poppy seed.
Batter will be thick.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Place right side up and glaze if desired.

title: potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes; cover with cold water and salt.
Boil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and chill.
Blend salad dressing and sour cream.
Add ingredients.
Mix and chill.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt chips, milk and oleo on low heat in a heavy pan.
Put peanuts and marshmallows in a large bowl and pour the chips and milk mixture over them; mix well.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Brown onion in shortening.
Add seasonings and chicken.
Brown 10 minutes.
Add water, cover and let simmer slowly until tender. Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to drippings in pan and mix well. Replace chicken and heat through.
Do not boil again.
To thicken gravy, add 1 tablespoon flour blended in cold water until smooth. Serve with dumplings or bow ties.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
In large pan, melt butter and saute onion.
When onion becomes opaque, add flour and stir (as if making gravy).
Add bouillon, milk, broth, salt and pepper.
Add vegetables and chicken.
Pour into large baking dish and cover with pie crust.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° or until crust is golden.

title: chocolate crinkle
directions: Mix together.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Shape 1 teaspoon of dough into ball.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in milk in microwave.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered wax paper.
Chill.
Melt milk chocolate; spread chocolate on top of each candy.
Makes around 3 1/2 dozen.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark in covered glass dish in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and put back in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Make sure bark is smooth.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls to harden.

title: south texas nachos
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Drain well. Rinse with cold water.
Peel and devein shrimp; chop coarsely.
Combine shrimp with chilies, olives, cheese, onions and mayonnaise.
Place tortilla chips on a baking sheet; top with 1 1/2 teaspoons shrimp mixture. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Fry sausage with onion and drain.
Pour the meat mixture into a slow cooker or deep pan.
Drain 2 cans of beans before adding the remaining beans and ingredients to the sausage mixture.
Cook on medium heat.

title: beef eggrolls
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain.
Drain bean sprouts; add to meat.
Add cabbage and about half bottle soy sauce or to your liking.
Cook until cabbage just begins to wilt.
Heat oil.
Read instructions on eggroll wrappers to see how to fold them.
Fry to a golden brown.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish layer ham. Sprinkle with onion, flour, salt, pepper and potatoes.
Pour some of the milk over layer to moisten.
Repeat this process until all ingredients are gone.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 45 minutes or until potatoes are soft.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar together, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are slightly brown.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Line 9 x 13 dish with 2/3 of crushed chips. Pour chicken mixture over chips. Sprinkle with cheese. Top with remaining chips. Pour chicken broth over entire casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender. When cool, alternate layers of carrots, onion and pepper. Blend remaining ingredients. Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well for days.

title: apple pie
directions: Arrange apples in pie crust; sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over apples.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar with flour and cinnamon. Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Add margarine to top of mixture and place top crust over all.
Bake in microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Then bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: greek tea biscuits
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs well.
Add raisins, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda, milk and flour.
Mix thoroughly and toss on lightly floured board.
Roll very thin; cut into desired shapes and put on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or lightly brown.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cut up potatoes and put into a good size pot.
Pour in the 2 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 stick of butter.
Place over medium heat and stir until thickened.
When thickened, add the canned milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla flavoring; stir in.
Let simmer over low heat, continuing to stir, until ready to serve.

title: sin cake
directions: Mix with fork.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain liquid from beets into measuring cup. Add enough water so that beet liquid measures 2/3 of a cup. Set aside.

title: cheddar potatoes
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes.
Pour into a 1 or 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mint ice
directions: Boil water and sugar for 10 minutes.
Mix lemon juice, salt, mint and desired amount of food color.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into ice tray.
Freeze to mushy consistency.
Remove from tray.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Return to tray and freeze until firm.

title: french onion soup
directions: Microwave onions and margarine on High for 14 to 15 minutes in a deep 3-quart covered casserole dish, stirring 3 times.
Stir in salt, pepper, flour and paprika until well blended.
Add broth, water and bay leaf.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes, until boiling.
Let stand in oven 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and discard bay leaf.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine cream cheese and sour cream. Mix in Italian Dressing mix and shrimp.
Add onion and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain and rinse well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Simmer for thirty minutes.
Seal while hot.
Makes 7 pints.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice
directions: Place broth in crock-pot.
Put in rice, then celery, then onion.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour soup over all, cook until rice is tender and chicken is done.
Cook on low temperature.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate.

title: cherry swirl coffee cake
directions: Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Spread 2/3 of the batter in greased jelly roll pan.
Spread 1 can of pie filling over batter. Drop remaining batter by tablespoon onto pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze while warm.

title: garden quiche
directions: Roll out pie pastry.
Shape into 9-inch pie plate.
Prick sides and bottom with fork to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Place half of the shredded cheese in pastry shell.
Layer mushrooms on cheese, then onion and green pepper.
Place eggs in bowl.
Attach bowl and wire whip.
On speed 4, whip for 2 minutes.
Blend in cream, salt, parsley and hot pepper sauce.
On speed 2, blend about 1 minute.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale before serving.
You can use lime jello if you want green punch.

title: sausage-cheese bread
directions: Roll dough in a large rectangular shape.
Mix together all other ingredients in a bowl.
Spread over dough and roll up like a jelly roll.
Pinch ends and top together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta - tuna salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together the mayonnaise, vinegar and pepper until smooth.
Add macaroni, tuna, peas, celery, onion and dill.
Toss to coat well.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Combine butter, sugars and spices; beat well until light and fluffy.
Add ice cream, stirring until well blended.
Spoon into a 2-quart freezer container.
Freeze.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour; heat oil in a large skillet and brown chicken.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until chicken is done, basting occasionally.

title: cob web
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour melted chocolate over mixture on a cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Let set until they harden.

title: spinach balls
directions: Defrost spinach.
Place in bowl.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Make 1-inch balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Chill macaroni and vegetables. Combine with bacon and half of the onions crumbled. Add Miracle Whip, parsley flakes and seasoned salt. Chill. Add rest of onions on top before serving.

title: curried wheat snacks
directions: Melt butter in large skillet. Blend in seasonings. Add Shredded Wheat and toss. Heat about 5 minutes over low heat, stirring frequently. Drain on paper towels. Serve warm.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Save 1 cup broth.
Tear chicken off bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Set aside. After baking cornbread, let cool and crumble.
Pour melted margarine over cornbread and mix well.
To chicken, add both cans of soup and cup of chicken broth.
In the bottom of baking dish, put a little more than half of the cornbread mixture.
Then spoon meat mixture onto cornbread.
Slice boiled eggs and put on top of this.
Then add remaining cornbread.
Bake at 325° until golden brown and bubbly.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pineapple and carrots.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost.

title: applesauce meat loaf(low-fat and diabetic meal)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and place in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 90 minutes.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Boil all the ingredients together, then add in the carrots.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Add liquid and boil until thick and shiny. Remove from heat and add margarine and salt. Pour over beets. Can be served hot or cold.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, oil, pineapple, and egg yolks, cinnamon and water; mix well.
Add nuts.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: walnut jumbos
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses and mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add oats and chopped nuts.
Drop by tablespoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes before removing.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, water, 1 tablespoon parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and basil, oregano, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 25 minutes.
In another bowl, mix 1/4 of Mozzarella cheese and mix with cottage cheese, egg and remaining parsley, salt, basil.
In 9 x 13 pan, layer 1/4 meat sauce, 3 noodles (cooked), 1/3 cottage cheese mixture, 1/3 Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Repeat layering 2 more times. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: noodle souffle
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese, butter, lemon juice, sugar, salt and eggs until smooth and well blended.
Stir in warm noodles.
Pour mixture into 3-quart buttered souffle dish.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Turn onto platter. Serves 6.

title: ziti
directions: Bring a large pot of water to boil, add ziti noodles and cook until tender, but still firm to the bite (uncovered).
Drain and set aside.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Combine mix and oil. Add spices.
Pour over crackers in large roasting pan; stir to coat.
Place in warm oven (300°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keep in tightly closed container.

title: carmels
directions: Cook to 242° in a deep heavy pan.
Pour quickly into a buttered 10 inch pie pan.
Works best if you double the recipe.

title: chicken breasts and stove top stuffing
directions: Spray or butter an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Lay chicken in a layer. Put Swiss cheese on top of chicken.
Put mushrooms on top.
Take can of soup and mix with wine.
Do not add water.
Put soup and wine on top of chicken mixture.
Make 1 package of stuffing.
Cool and crumble or spread on top of chicken.
Dot with butter over top of stuffing.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Uncover last 10 minutes to crisp it.
Use tinfoil to cover pan.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Spray a 9 x 10-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake in 425° oven until golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Season hamburger well with salt and pepper and add well beaten egg.
Mix well and combine with rice.
Melt shortening; add onion and cook several minutes.
Combine tomato soup with equal amount of water and add to onion.
Add parsley, celery, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper and cook 10 minutes.
Wash cabbage leaves and boil until tender.
Put 2 tablespoons meat mixture in each leaf and roll tightly.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place in saucepan (or crock-pot) and pour sauce over rolls.
Cover pan tightly and cook slowly 3 hours.
Serve very hot.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred all above, sprinkle salt over and let stand 1 hour.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ham, pork, eggs, milk, corn flakes and pepper.
Press into baking pan.
Mix brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and water.
Pour over loaf and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fantasy fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with chunks of cantaloupe, honeydew melon, peaches or nectarines.
Great for dieters.

title: fudge pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then bake 40 minutes at 300°.

title: easy custard pie
directions: *The dime store has handy plastic separators for inexperienced guys so you don't have to ask mother for help.

title: grandma adams potato candy
directions: Boil potatoes the size of an egg.
Peel and mash potatoes while warm.
Mix powdered sugar into potato.
Add vanilla.
Roll dough out on powdered sugar board.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll dough up.
Let get firm.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: spinach-yogurt dip
directions: In a blender or
food processor, whirl garlic and green onion with spinach until finely chopped.
Add rest of ingredients and blend to mix well.
Taste and adjust seasonings.

title: pizza dip
directions: Blend and mix cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and garlic powder.
Spread evenly throughout a pie dish. Add the pizza sauce first, then the onions and green peppers.
Lastly, layer the Mozzarella cheese on top and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat batter in order given.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in a tightly covered container. To prepare beverage, put 1 teaspoon mix in a cup and fill with boiling water.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grind the first 4 ingredients together.
Add the last 2 ingredients and spread on hamburger buns or English muffins.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon in bowl.
In another bowl, mix sugar and eggs; add oil, then add flour mixture.
Add pumpkin and nuts.
Put in greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; cool.
In bowl, beat together 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar. Continue beating until thick and lemon colored.
Stir together flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt; add to egg mixture. Beat well.
Blend in chocolate mixture and nuts; set aside.
Cream together cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar until fluffy.
Blend in remaining egg and vanilla.
Spread half of the chocolate mixture in a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour cheese mixture over; top with remaining chocolate mixture.
Swirl layers to marble.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into sixteen squares.

title: sweet potato cake with cream frosting
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add slowly to oil mixture.
Divide mixture into two 8-inch cake pans that have been oiled and lined with waxed paper.
Bake 40 minutes or until tests done.
Cool before frosting.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and persimmon pulp and mix. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Wash peas; soak 4 hours.
Cover with water.
Add all ingredients; cook 2 hours, covered, over low heat.
Serve with cornbread.

title: pineapple pecan cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, eggs and pineapple.
Mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.	Use with Pineapple Pecan Cake Frosting.

title: fried sausage
directions: In large skillet, put enough water to coat bottom.
Puncture sausage with fork.
Place in pan.
Cook sausage over low flame until brown on both sides.
Serve with lemon juice.

title: yummy vegetables
directions: Arrange the onions, celery, carrots and cabbage in saucepan in layers as listed.
Sprinkle the sugar, salt, margarine and water over vegetables.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Mix beans. Add pepper, onion, celery and pimento if desired. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 12 to 48 hours.
Drain and serve.
Salad will keep for several days in the refrigerator.
Dressing ingredients may be varied to suit taste.
Number of servings:

title: thai noodle soup
directions: Place chopped chicken in 1/2-quart of cold water and chicken stock.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add noodles, chopped celery leaves, bean sprouts and green onions.
Simmer and serve while hot.

title: herb broiled tomatoes
directions: Place tomato halves in shallow baking pan and season with salt, pepper and marjoram.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with parsley.
Broil 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Cool and peel sweet potatoes.
Mix together sweet potatoes, brown sugar, Bisquick mix and water.
Combine thoroughly (the mixture will be more moist than regular biscuits).
Flour surface. Roll biscuit mix to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Place on greased sheet pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.
